1
00:00:31,553 --> 00:00:35,600
[Birds chirping]

2
00:00:52,487 --> 00:00:55,011
[Autje] This story ends
before you were born.

3
00:01:12,202 --> 00:01:13,595
Mother.

4
00:01:14,857 --> 00:01:17,120
[Eerie music playing]

5
00:01:19,166 --> 00:01:20,491
Again.

6
00:01:20,515 --> 00:01:22,560
[Agata speaking indistinctly]

7
00:01:23,866 --> 00:01:25,278
[Autje] When we woke up

8
00:01:25,302 --> 00:01:27,976
feeling hands that
were no longer there,

9
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,699
the elders told us
that it was the work of ghosts

10
00:01:31,395 --> 00:01:32,570
or Satan.

11
00:01:33,223 --> 00:01:35,138
[Eerie music fades]

12
00:01:36,444 --> 00:01:39,988
Or that we were lying
to get attention.

13
00:01:40,012 --> 00:01:43,451
Or that it was an act
of wild female imagination.

14
00:01:49,283 --> 00:01:50,719
It went on for years.

15
00:01:53,461 --> 00:01:54,636
To all of us.

16
00:02:04,211 --> 00:02:06,145
It felt like weightlessness.

17
00:02:06,169 --> 00:02:07,799
[Girl laughing]

18
00:02:07,823 --> 00:02:10,217
It felt like drifting over
what used to be real.

19
00:02:13,394 --> 00:02:16,373
- [Girl speaking indistinctly]
- It felt like a banishment,

20
00:02:16,397 --> 00:02:18,070
as though we had
no invitation anymore

21
00:02:18,094 --> 00:02:19,922
to be a part of the real.

22
00:02:23,926 --> 00:02:25,841
[Girl speaking indistinctly]

23
00:02:29,584 --> 00:02:31,083
I used to wonder who I would be

24
00:02:31,107 --> 00:02:33,955
if it hadn't happened to me.

25
00:02:33,979 --> 00:02:36,460
I used to miss the person
I might have been.

26
00:02:37,592 --> 00:02:39,115
I don't anymore.

27
00:02:41,813 --> 00:02:43,443
Because it's doomsday

28
00:02:43,467 --> 00:02:44,947
and a call to prayer.

29
00:02:46,209 --> 00:02:47,341
It's both.

30
00:02:49,778 --> 00:02:52,172
- [Suspenseful music playing]
- [Man panting]

31
00:02:54,478 --> 00:02:55,827
We caught one of them.

32
00:02:56,437 --> 00:02:57,873
I saw his face.

33
00:02:59,091 --> 00:03:00,745
And then he named the others.

34
00:03:02,007 --> 00:03:03,226
[Man] Come on.

35
00:03:04,184 --> 00:03:05,291
[Screaming]

36
00:03:05,315 --> 00:03:07,250
[Grunting]

37
00:03:07,274 --> 00:03:08,318
[Man gasps]

38
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:11,147
[Man groaning]

39
00:03:12,279 --> 00:03:13,517
[Autje] Eventually the attackers

40
00:03:13,541 --> 00:03:15,780
were taken to the police
in the city

41
00:03:15,804 --> 00:03:17,173
for their own protection.

42
00:03:17,197 --> 00:03:19,155
[Screaming]

43
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:26,530
Almost all of the men
of the colony

44
00:03:26,554 --> 00:03:27,792
went to the city to post bail

45
00:03:27,816 --> 00:03:29,165
for the attackers.

46
00:03:30,079 --> 00:03:31,578
We were given two days

47
00:03:31,602 --> 00:03:33,822
to forgive the attackers
before they returned.

48
00:03:36,303 --> 00:03:37,758
If we did not forgive them

49
00:03:37,782 --> 00:03:39,934
we would be ordered
to leave the colony

50
00:03:39,958 --> 00:03:42,894
and be denied entry
into the kingdom of heaven.

51
00:03:42,918 --> 00:03:44,006
[Suspenseful music stops]

52
00:03:54,277 --> 00:03:55,452
[Neitje] Do nothing.

53
00:03:58,325 --> 00:03:59,413
[Salome] Stay and fight.

54
00:04:02,851 --> 00:04:03,852
[Both] Leave.

55
00:04:04,853 --> 00:04:05,893
[Melancholy music playing]

56
00:04:09,423 --> 00:04:12,208
[Women panting]

57
00:04:19,737 --> 00:04:20,758
[Woman 1 sobbing]

58
00:04:20,782 --> 00:04:22,349
[Woman 2 speaking indistinctly]

59
00:04:32,184 --> 00:04:35,599
[Autje] Girls in our colony
had very little schooling.

60
00:04:35,623 --> 00:04:38,016
We hardly knew
how to read or to write.

61
00:04:38,887 --> 00:04:40,517
But that day,

62
00:04:40,541 --> 00:04:41,996
we learned how to vote.

63
00:04:42,020 --> 00:04:43,239
[Baby crying]

64
00:04:45,589 --> 00:04:48,113
[Indistinct talking]

65
00:05:36,423 --> 00:05:37,791
The vote was tied between

66
00:05:37,815 --> 00:05:40,838
staying and fighting,
or leaving.

67
00:05:40,862 --> 00:05:43,754
So three families
including yours and mine

68
00:05:43,778 --> 00:05:45,146
were elected to decide

69
00:05:45,170 --> 00:05:46,911
what the women
of the colony would do.

70
00:05:56,660 --> 00:05:59,770
Your mother had asked,
August, the school teacher,

71
00:05:59,794 --> 00:06:02,207
to take the minutes
of our meeting.

72
00:06:02,231 --> 00:06:06,124
August came back to the colony
just recently.

73
00:06:06,148 --> 00:06:09,107
His family had been
excommunicated years ago.

74
00:06:17,638 --> 00:06:20,510
August had loved your mother
since he was a boy.

75
00:06:22,077 --> 00:06:24,427
[Chuckles softly]

76
00:06:38,006 --> 00:06:39,505
Before we began,

77
00:06:39,529 --> 00:06:41,159
your grandmother, agata,

78
00:06:41,183 --> 00:06:43,533
told us we had to honor
our service to each other.

79
00:06:44,665 --> 00:06:47,165
We had to represent it.

80
00:06:47,189 --> 00:06:48,862
Just as the disciples
were washed

81
00:06:48,886 --> 00:06:51,517
by Jesus at the last supper,

82
00:06:51,541 --> 00:06:54,109
knowing that his hour had come.

83
00:06:57,721 --> 00:06:59,438
We only had 24 hours

84
00:06:59,462 --> 00:07:02,334
to imagine what world
you would be born into.

85
00:07:03,292 --> 00:07:04,293
[Melancholic music fades]

86
00:07:06,121 --> 00:07:08,316
[Scarface janz] It is a part
of our faith to forgive.

87
00:07:08,340 --> 00:07:10,231
We have always forgiven those
who have wronged us.

88
00:07:10,255 --> 00:07:11,319
Why not now?

89
00:07:11,343 --> 00:07:12,799
Because now we know better.

90
00:07:12,823 --> 00:07:14,410
We will be excommunicated,

91
00:07:14,434 --> 00:07:16,107
forced to leave the colony
in disgrace

92
00:07:16,131 --> 00:07:17,785
if we do not forgive these men.

93
00:07:18,786 --> 00:07:20,198
And if we are excommunicated,

94
00:07:20,222 --> 00:07:23,157
we forfeit our place in heaven.

95
00:07:23,181 --> 00:07:26,422
How could any of you
live with the fear of that?

96
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:28,622
[Agata] These are
legitimate fears.

97
00:07:29,971 --> 00:07:31,470
How can we address them?

98
00:07:31,494 --> 00:07:33,994
[Scarface janz] The only
important thing to establish

99
00:07:34,018 --> 00:07:35,933
is if we forgive the men.

100
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:39,391
So that we will be allowed
to enter the gates of heaven.

101
00:07:39,415 --> 00:07:40,784
[Scoffs]

102
00:07:40,808 --> 00:07:42,176
[Mariche] You can laugh
all you like, salome,

103
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,526
but we will be forced
to leave the colony

104
00:07:43,550 --> 00:07:44,670
if we don't forgive the men.

105
00:07:45,813 --> 00:07:47,138
How will the lord
when he arrives

106
00:07:47,162 --> 00:07:48,879
find the women
if we aren't in the colony?

107
00:07:48,903 --> 00:07:50,489
Jesus is able to return to life,

108
00:07:50,513 --> 00:07:51,882
live for thousands of years

109
00:07:51,906 --> 00:07:53,361
and then drop down
to earth from heaven

110
00:07:53,385 --> 00:07:54,580
to scoop up his supporters,

111
00:07:54,604 --> 00:07:56,277
surely he'd also
be able to locate

112
00:07:56,301 --> 00:07:57,409
a few women
who left their colony.

113
00:07:57,433 --> 00:07:58,497
Let's stay on track.

114
00:07:58,521 --> 00:07:59,716
All right. I'll stay on track.

115
00:07:59,740 --> 00:08:01,631
I cannot forgive them.

116
00:08:01,655 --> 00:08:03,352
I will never forgive them.

117
00:08:04,571 --> 00:08:05,876
I can't either.

118
00:08:07,617 --> 00:08:08,768
But we want to enter

119
00:08:08,792 --> 00:08:10,074
the kingdom of heaven
when we die.

120
00:08:10,098 --> 00:08:11,316
[Grunts]

121
00:08:14,668 --> 00:08:16,341
We have everything we want here.

122
00:08:16,365 --> 00:08:17,516
[Salome] No.

123
00:08:17,540 --> 00:08:18,846
Want less.

124
00:08:19,629 --> 00:08:21,041
[Scoffs]

125
00:08:21,065 --> 00:08:22,347
Does entering
the kingdom of heaven

126
00:08:22,371 --> 00:08:24,001
mean nothing to any of you?

127
00:08:24,025 --> 00:08:25,568
Surely there must be something

128
00:08:25,592 --> 00:08:28,135
worth living for in this life,
not only in the next.

129
00:08:28,159 --> 00:08:29,378
- [Scoffs]
- [Chuckles]

130
00:08:40,432 --> 00:08:42,019
Autje!

131
00:08:42,043 --> 00:08:43,281
- See you soon. It's all right.
- [Helena] Sorry.

132
00:08:43,305 --> 00:08:44,872
It's all right.
It will be all right.

133
00:08:54,229 --> 00:08:56,337
[Autje] Your grandmother
used to say,

134
00:08:56,361 --> 00:08:58,426
"find out where
you can be of help

135
00:08:58,450 --> 00:09:00,757
"and leave what
you can't help behind."

136
00:09:01,889 --> 00:09:02,996
I think that's easier

137
00:09:03,020 --> 00:09:04,737
when you're old like her.

138
00:09:04,761 --> 00:09:06,826
[Agata] So we must decide now

139
00:09:06,850 --> 00:09:09,916
to stay and fight, or leave.

140
00:09:09,940 --> 00:09:12,160
Those are the options
in front of us.

141
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:15,816
We will not do nothing.

142
00:09:19,341 --> 00:09:22,431
I want to talk about
my horses Ruth and Cheryl.

143
00:09:24,389 --> 00:09:26,019
[Dogs barking]

144
00:09:26,043 --> 00:09:27,804
When Ruth and Cheryl
are frightened by dueck's dogs

145
00:09:27,828 --> 00:09:30,676
on the mile road
that leads to the church,

146
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:32,615
their initial instinct
is to bolt.

147
00:09:33,834 --> 00:09:34,922
Whoa!

148
00:09:36,663 --> 00:09:38,641
These horses
don't organize meetings

149
00:09:38,665 --> 00:09:40,623
to decide what they will do.

150
00:09:41,102 --> 00:09:42,209
They run.

151
00:09:42,233 --> 00:09:44,560
But, Greta, we are not animals.

152
00:09:44,584 --> 00:09:46,866
We have been preyed upon
like animals.

153
00:09:46,890 --> 00:09:49,347
Maybe we should respond
like animals.

154
00:09:49,371 --> 00:09:50,435
[Agata] In my lifetime,
I have seen

155
00:09:50,459 --> 00:09:52,393
horses confront angry dogs

156
00:09:52,417 --> 00:09:54,439
and try to stomp them to death.

157
00:09:54,463 --> 00:09:55,875
Animals don't always flee.

158
00:09:55,899 --> 00:09:57,573
Is this how we want
to teach our daughters

159
00:09:57,597 --> 00:09:59,226
to defend themselves?

160
00:09:59,250 --> 00:10:00,401
By fleeing?

161
00:10:00,425 --> 00:10:01,577
Not fleeing but leaving.

162
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:02,795
I was just talking
about leaving.

163
00:10:02,819 --> 00:10:03,927
[Salome] I would rather
stand my ground

164
00:10:03,951 --> 00:10:05,102
and shoot each man in the heart

165
00:10:05,126 --> 00:10:06,538
and Bury 'em in a pit than flee.

166
00:10:06,562 --> 00:10:08,192
And I'll deal with god's wrath
if I have to.

167
00:10:08,216 --> 00:10:09,976
Salome, aunt Greta is talking
about leaving not fleeing.

168
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,848
The word "fleeing"
wasn't what she meant.

169
00:10:11,872 --> 00:10:14,894
Yeah. Please forgive my mother
for using the wrong word.

170
00:10:14,918 --> 00:10:16,113
It's a sin so outrageous

171
00:10:16,137 --> 00:10:17,723
that salome has taken it
upon herself

172
00:10:17,747 --> 00:10:19,943
to rectify for the sake
of all humanity.

173
00:10:19,967 --> 00:10:22,467
[Agata] "Leaving" and "fleeing"
are different words

174
00:10:22,491 --> 00:10:24,556
with different meanings.

175
00:10:24,580 --> 00:10:26,669
They each say
something about us.

176
00:10:32,196 --> 00:10:33,870
August,

177
00:10:33,894 --> 00:10:36,046
what do you make of all of this?

178
00:10:36,070 --> 00:10:37,898
Do you have an opinion too?

179
00:10:39,551 --> 00:10:40,596
I think...

180
00:10:42,424 --> 00:10:44,663
I think that it is possible

181
00:10:44,687 --> 00:10:46,776
to leave something or someone...

182
00:10:49,561 --> 00:10:51,931
In one frame of mind

183
00:10:51,955 --> 00:10:55,413
and arrive elsewhere in another

184
00:10:55,437 --> 00:10:58,024
entirely unexpected
frame of mind.

185
00:10:58,048 --> 00:10:59,809
I want to stay and fight.

186
00:10:59,833 --> 00:11:01,071
But won't we lose the fight
to the men

187
00:11:01,095 --> 00:11:03,073
and be forced
to forgive them anyway?

188
00:11:03,097 --> 00:11:04,422
I want to stay and fight too.

189
00:11:04,446 --> 00:11:05,945
[Mariche] No one's surprised
that you do.

190
00:11:05,969 --> 00:11:07,512
All you do is fight.

191
00:11:07,536 --> 00:11:09,296
Is this really
how we are to decide

192
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:11,647
the fates of all the women
in this colony? [Scoffs]

193
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,126
Just another vote

194
00:11:13,150 --> 00:11:15,215
where we put an x
next to our position?

195
00:11:15,239 --> 00:11:17,043
I thought we were here
to do more than that.

196
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:18,305
You mean talk more about

197
00:11:18,329 --> 00:11:19,350
forgiving the men
and doing nothing.

198
00:11:19,374 --> 00:11:20,743
Everything else is insane.

199
00:11:20,767 --> 00:11:22,527
But none of you
will listen to reason.

200
00:11:22,551 --> 00:11:24,224
Well, why are you here with us?

201
00:11:24,248 --> 00:11:25,661
Why are you still here with us
if that is what you believe?

202
00:11:25,685 --> 00:11:27,097
Just leave with the rest
of the do nothing women.

203
00:11:27,121 --> 00:11:30,080
She is my daughter
and I want her here with us.

204
00:11:32,039 --> 00:11:33,625
Is forgiveness
that's forced upon us

205
00:11:33,649 --> 00:11:34,737
true forgiveness?

206
00:11:35,129 --> 00:11:36,933
[Sighs]

207
00:11:36,957 --> 00:11:39,176
[Salome] Keep nonsense
like that to yourself please.

208
00:11:39,742 --> 00:11:40,893
Autje, get down!

209
00:11:40,917 --> 00:11:42,919
[Greta] Autje,
listen to your mother!

210
00:11:43,615 --> 00:11:44,767
Behave yourself.

211
00:11:44,791 --> 00:11:46,551
Don't you hear
the rafter's creaking?

212
00:11:46,575 --> 00:11:48,446
Do you want the roof to cave in?

213
00:11:52,450 --> 00:11:54,191
[Autje] Many of us
saw ourselves from above.

214
00:11:56,150 --> 00:11:57,823
I'm not sure if it was god

215
00:11:57,847 --> 00:12:00,545
and we were seeing ourselves
through his eyes.

216
00:12:01,198 --> 00:12:02,349
[Clanging]

217
00:12:02,373 --> 00:12:04,375
Or if we just couldn't be there.

218
00:12:07,074 --> 00:12:08,791
In our own bodies.

219
00:12:08,815 --> 00:12:10,077
[Melancholic music playing]

220
00:12:12,775 --> 00:12:13,926
[Neitje] How'd you get up there?

221
00:12:13,950 --> 00:12:15,362
[Autje] It was a miracle.

222
00:12:15,386 --> 00:12:17,713
[Neitje chuckles]
A miracle from god.

223
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:19,377
- [Autje] Of course.
- [Neitje] What else?

224
00:12:20,348 --> 00:12:22,369
[Autje] Where I come from,

225
00:12:22,393 --> 00:12:24,134
where your mother comes from,

226
00:12:25,309 --> 00:12:28,419
we didn't talk about our bodies.

227
00:12:28,443 --> 00:12:29,942
So when something
like this happened

228
00:12:29,966 --> 00:12:32,510
there was no language for it.

229
00:12:32,534 --> 00:12:36,277
And without language for it,
there was a gaping silence.

230
00:12:38,061 --> 00:12:41,108
And in that gaping silence
was the real horror.

231
00:13:01,737 --> 00:13:04,174
[Sobbing]

232
00:13:46,782 --> 00:13:48,238
Neitje's mother hanged herself

233
00:13:48,262 --> 00:13:50,960
after the attacks
had gone on for a while.

234
00:13:53,180 --> 00:13:55,027
It made us wonder,

235
00:13:55,051 --> 00:13:56,855
why did our feet
keep moving forward

236
00:13:56,879 --> 00:13:58,446
when hers just couldn't.

237
00:13:59,577 --> 00:14:00,859
What sets us apart

238
00:14:00,883 --> 00:14:02,711
from the ones
who get left behind?

239
00:14:04,060 --> 00:14:05,061
[Melancholic music fades]

240
00:14:07,455 --> 00:14:09,259
This is never going to end.

241
00:14:09,283 --> 00:14:11,043
We'll be dead
and they'll still be talking.

242
00:14:11,067 --> 00:14:12,523
Or worse.
We'll have to live through it.

243
00:14:12,547 --> 00:14:13,635
[Chuckles softly]

244
00:14:15,071 --> 00:14:16,440
[Ona] August, I think
you should make lists

245
00:14:16,464 --> 00:14:18,659
of the pros and cons
of both options.

246
00:14:18,683 --> 00:14:21,077
"Staying and fighting"
and "leaving."

247
00:14:24,559 --> 00:14:26,082
Post it on the wall.

248
00:14:29,607 --> 00:14:30,889
Make sure and write large.

249
00:14:30,913 --> 00:14:32,021
[Mejal] Why?

250
00:14:32,045 --> 00:14:33,892
We can't read it.

251
00:14:33,916 --> 00:14:35,328
No, but we'll keep it here
as an artifact

252
00:14:35,352 --> 00:14:37,093
for others to discover.

253
00:14:39,269 --> 00:14:40,768
I think the first heading
should say,

254
00:14:40,792 --> 00:14:43,206
"staying and fighting"
and under that write "pros".

255
00:14:43,230 --> 00:14:45,208
[Agata] Who will go first?

256
00:14:45,232 --> 00:14:47,340
We're starting with
staying and fighting, pros.

257
00:14:47,364 --> 00:14:49,714
Why do we need this?
This is our home.

258
00:14:51,194 --> 00:14:52,302
[Mariche]
That's what you believe,

259
00:14:52,326 --> 00:14:54,043
it's not what everyone believes.

260
00:14:54,067 --> 00:14:55,261
- Excuse me.
- [All arguing]

261
00:14:55,285 --> 00:14:57,002
[August] Forgive me.
Excuse me, um...

262
00:14:57,026 --> 00:14:59,918
May I request that you
take it in turns speaking

263
00:14:59,942 --> 00:15:02,529
so that I can understand
what each of you is saying.

264
00:15:02,553 --> 00:15:03,748
It takes me
a second to transcribe.

265
00:15:03,772 --> 00:15:05,184
Should we put up our hands

266
00:15:05,208 --> 00:15:07,008
as though we are children
in your schoolhouse?

267
00:15:08,037 --> 00:15:09,188
I...

268
00:15:09,212 --> 00:15:10,929
I apologize.

269
00:15:10,953 --> 00:15:13,105
We won't have to leave.

270
00:15:13,129 --> 00:15:14,783
- Sorry.
- Will you just write it down?

271
00:15:15,523 --> 00:15:16,674
Under pros.

272
00:15:16,698 --> 00:15:18,937
Salome has had a brilliant idea

273
00:15:18,961 --> 00:15:20,939
that if we stay
we won't have to leave.

274
00:15:20,963 --> 00:15:22,462
[Mejal] We won't
have to figure out

275
00:15:22,486 --> 00:15:24,073
where we are going
or experience the uncertainty

276
00:15:24,097 --> 00:15:26,336
of not knowing
where we are going.

277
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,424
We don't have a map.

278
00:15:27,448 --> 00:15:28,860
[Salome] That's absurd.

279
00:15:28,884 --> 00:15:30,470
The only certainty we'll know
is uncertainty,

280
00:15:30,494 --> 00:15:32,255
no matter where we are.

281
00:15:32,279 --> 00:15:33,734
[Agata] Neitje? Autje?

282
00:15:33,758 --> 00:15:35,935
Do you have something
to add to the list?

283
00:15:37,632 --> 00:15:39,610
We won't have
to leave the people we love.

284
00:15:39,634 --> 00:15:41,699
Well, we could bring
our loved ones

285
00:15:41,723 --> 00:15:43,266
with us if we leave.

286
00:15:43,290 --> 00:15:44,920
How?

287
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:47,574
What does that mean?
That we move the whole colony?

288
00:15:47,598 --> 00:15:49,141
What could that possibly mean?

289
00:15:49,165 --> 00:15:51,535
[Agata] We could create
the possibility of a new order

290
00:15:51,559 --> 00:15:54,973
right here in a place
that is familiar to us.

291
00:15:54,997 --> 00:15:57,802
[Salome] Not simply familiar,
but a place that is ours.

292
00:15:57,826 --> 00:15:59,456
[Mejal] Do we need
to write the cons?

293
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:02,024
Isn't it obvious
that we must stay and fight?

294
00:16:02,048 --> 00:16:04,833
Cons. We won't be forgiven.

295
00:16:06,052 --> 00:16:07,444
May I say something?

296
00:16:08,489 --> 00:16:09,683
Please.

297
00:16:09,707 --> 00:16:11,120
Would it be a good idea
before we list

298
00:16:11,144 --> 00:16:12,991
the pros and cons
of "staying and fighting"

299
00:16:13,015 --> 00:16:14,688
to talk about exactly what it is

300
00:16:14,712 --> 00:16:15,951
we're fighting for?

301
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:17,387
[Salome] It's obvious.

302
00:16:17,411 --> 00:16:18,605
We are fighting for our safety

303
00:16:18,629 --> 00:16:19,911
and for our freedom
from attacks.

304
00:16:19,935 --> 00:16:22,566
[Ona] But what would
that mean to us?

305
00:16:22,590 --> 00:16:24,350
Perhaps we need a statement
which describes

306
00:16:24,374 --> 00:16:25,743
what we want the colony
to be like

307
00:16:25,767 --> 00:16:27,658
after winning the fight.

308
00:16:27,682 --> 00:16:29,138
Perhaps we need
to understand more

309
00:16:29,162 --> 00:16:30,704
what it is
we are fighting to achieve,

310
00:16:30,728 --> 00:16:33,272
not only what we are fighting
to destroy.

311
00:16:33,296 --> 00:16:34,839
- [Groans]
- [Chuckles]

312
00:16:34,863 --> 00:16:36,710
Are we staying or are we going?

313
00:16:36,734 --> 00:16:37,779
[Laughing]

314
00:16:39,389 --> 00:16:40,758
Ona, please tell us more

315
00:16:40,782 --> 00:16:43,002
about the statement
you're thinking about.

316
00:16:46,092 --> 00:16:47,373
Men and women would make

317
00:16:47,397 --> 00:16:50,009
all decisions
for the colony collectively.

318
00:16:51,097 --> 00:16:53,727
Women would be allowed to think.

319
00:16:53,751 --> 00:16:57,427
Girls will be taught
to read and to write.

320
00:16:57,451 --> 00:16:59,646
The schoolhouse must display
a map of the world

321
00:16:59,670 --> 00:17:02,998
so that we can begin
to understand our place in it.

322
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:05,174
A new religion,
taken from the old

323
00:17:05,198 --> 00:17:07,026
but focused on love

324
00:17:08,462 --> 00:17:10,942
would be created
by the women of the colony.

325
00:17:12,118 --> 00:17:13,771
Our children would be safe.

326
00:17:17,558 --> 00:17:18,994
"Collectively."

327
00:17:22,563 --> 00:17:24,565
You sound like August's mother.

328
00:17:28,438 --> 00:17:29,874
[Chuckles softly]

329
00:17:31,006 --> 00:17:32,703
Ona, you're a dreamer.

330
00:17:33,748 --> 00:17:36,031
We're women without a voice.

331
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:37,423
We have nothing to return to.

332
00:17:37,447 --> 00:17:39,382
Even the animals
are safer in their homes

333
00:17:39,406 --> 00:17:41,297
than we women are.

334
00:17:41,321 --> 00:17:43,560
All we have are our dreams.

335
00:17:43,584 --> 00:17:45,499
So of course we are dreamers.

336
00:17:46,848 --> 00:17:48,415
And you want to hear my dream?

337
00:17:51,461 --> 00:17:53,570
I dream that people
who speak nonsense,

338
00:17:53,594 --> 00:17:55,093
who have no grasp on reality,

339
00:17:55,117 --> 00:17:57,337
are not put in charge
of making statements.

340
00:17:59,513 --> 00:18:02,013
What if the men
refuse to meet our demands?

341
00:18:02,037 --> 00:18:03,957
- [Autje and neitje giggling]
- [Bucket clanging]

342
00:18:03,995 --> 00:18:05,084
Sorry.

343
00:18:09,566 --> 00:18:10,698
We'll kill them.

344
00:18:11,916 --> 00:18:12,917
No, ona.

345
00:18:17,444 --> 00:18:19,010
[Laughing]

346
00:18:23,972 --> 00:18:25,123
What if the men
who are in prison

347
00:18:25,147 --> 00:18:26,148
are not guilty?

348
00:18:27,932 --> 00:18:28,977
[Eerie music playing]

349
00:18:29,499 --> 00:18:30,520
Mother?

350
00:18:30,544 --> 00:18:31,695
[Mariche] Autje.

351
00:18:31,719 --> 00:18:32,826
Why are you asking
if they're...?

352
00:18:32,850 --> 00:18:34,132
Autje, shush.

353
00:18:34,156 --> 00:18:35,307
We caught one of them.

354
00:18:35,331 --> 00:18:36,743
[Screaming]

355
00:18:36,767 --> 00:18:38,093
I saw him.

356
00:18:38,117 --> 00:18:39,529
[Mariche] But only one.

357
00:18:39,553 --> 00:18:41,139
[Salome] Yes, only one,
but he named the others.

358
00:18:41,163 --> 00:18:42,880
But what if he was lying?

359
00:18:42,904 --> 00:18:43,948
[Eerie music stops]

360
00:18:45,254 --> 00:18:46,623
We must consider this.

361
00:18:46,647 --> 00:18:49,887
No! That is not
our responsibility

362
00:18:49,911 --> 00:18:51,149
because we aren't in charge

363
00:18:51,173 --> 00:18:53,673
of whether or not
they are punished.

364
00:18:53,697 --> 00:18:55,458
We know that
we've been attacked by men.

365
00:18:55,482 --> 00:18:57,547
Not by ghosts or Satan

366
00:18:57,571 --> 00:18:59,288
as we were led to believe
for so long.

367
00:18:59,312 --> 00:19:02,639
We know that we've not
imagined these attacks.

368
00:19:02,663 --> 00:19:05,642
That we were made unconscious
with cow tranquilizer.

369
00:19:05,666 --> 00:19:09,080
We know that we are bruised,
and infected,

370
00:19:09,104 --> 00:19:12,605
and pregnant, and terrified,
and insane,

371
00:19:12,629 --> 00:19:14,781
and some of us are dead.

372
00:19:14,805 --> 00:19:17,175
We know that
we must protect our children.

373
00:19:17,199 --> 00:19:20,439
Regardless of who is guilty.

374
00:19:20,463 --> 00:19:24,119
All right, salome. Thank you.
Please, sit down, hmm.

375
00:19:25,555 --> 00:19:26,556
Hmm.

376
00:19:48,926 --> 00:19:50,276
Shall we move on?

377
00:19:52,278 --> 00:19:53,820
It is possible the men in prison

378
00:19:53,844 --> 00:19:55,300
are not guilty of the attacks,

379
00:19:55,324 --> 00:19:57,998
but are they guilty
of not stopping the attacks?

380
00:19:58,022 --> 00:19:59,217
Are they guilty of knowing

381
00:19:59,241 --> 00:20:00,740
about the attacks
and doing nothing?

382
00:20:00,764 --> 00:20:02,220
How should we know
what they're guilty of or not?

383
00:20:02,244 --> 00:20:03,787
[Ona] But we do know.

384
00:20:03,811 --> 00:20:06,224
We do know that the conditions
have been created by men

385
00:20:06,248 --> 00:20:08,618
and that these attacks
have been made possible

386
00:20:08,642 --> 00:20:11,360
because of the circumstances
of the colony.

387
00:20:11,384 --> 00:20:12,709
And those circumstances

388
00:20:12,733 --> 00:20:15,233
have been created
and ordained by the men.

389
00:20:15,257 --> 00:20:17,148
[Mariche] But wait,
aren't you suggesting

390
00:20:17,172 --> 00:20:19,846
that the attackers
are as much victims

391
00:20:19,870 --> 00:20:22,458
as the victims of the attacks?

392
00:20:22,482 --> 00:20:24,329
That all of us, men and women

393
00:20:24,353 --> 00:20:26,157
are victims of the circumstances

394
00:20:26,181 --> 00:20:28,314
from which the colony
has been created.

395
00:20:32,013 --> 00:20:33,599
In a sense, yes.

396
00:20:33,623 --> 00:20:36,931
So then, even if the court
finds them guilty or innocent,

397
00:20:38,193 --> 00:20:40,302
they are... [breathes shakily]

398
00:20:40,326 --> 00:20:42,110
After all innocent.

399
00:20:44,460 --> 00:20:46,201
Yes, I would say so.

400
00:20:49,248 --> 00:20:51,226
- The elders called them evil.
- [Ona] That's not true.

401
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:52,531
It's the elder's quest for power

402
00:20:52,555 --> 00:20:53,837
that is responsible.

403
00:20:53,861 --> 00:20:55,012
Because they needed
to have those...

404
00:20:55,036 --> 00:20:56,622
Those they'd have power over.

405
00:20:56,646 --> 00:20:58,145
And those people are us.

406
00:20:58,169 --> 00:20:59,843
[Agata] And they have taught
the lesson of power

407
00:20:59,867 --> 00:21:01,671
to the boys and men
of the colony,

408
00:21:01,695 --> 00:21:04,959
and the boys and men
have been excellent students.

409
00:21:06,090 --> 00:21:08,267
Don't we all
want some sort of power?

410
00:21:09,093 --> 00:21:10,269
I think so.

411
00:21:11,052 --> 00:21:12,227
But I'm not sure.

412
00:21:13,359 --> 00:21:14,708
But we caught them.

413
00:21:15,361 --> 00:21:16,666
We caught them.

414
00:21:18,189 --> 00:21:20,733
Yes, you did.

415
00:21:20,757 --> 00:21:23,258
Then why are you
making it so complicated?

416
00:21:23,282 --> 00:21:26,285
This is very, very boring.

417
00:21:27,982 --> 00:21:29,897
We could ask the men to leave.

418
00:21:32,378 --> 00:21:34,293
Ask the men to leave?

419
00:21:37,774 --> 00:21:41,058
None of us have ever
asked the men for anything.

420
00:21:41,082 --> 00:21:42,649
Not a single thing.

421
00:21:44,041 --> 00:21:47,020
Not even for
the salt to be passed.

422
00:21:47,044 --> 00:21:50,589
Not even for a penny,
or a moment alone.

423
00:21:50,613 --> 00:21:54,071
Or to take the washing in,
or to open a curtain,

424
00:21:54,095 --> 00:21:57,248
or to go easy
on the small yearlings.

425
00:21:57,272 --> 00:21:59,903
Or to put your hand
on the small of my back

426
00:21:59,927 --> 00:22:03,167
while I try again
for the 12th or 13th time

427
00:22:03,191 --> 00:22:05,759
to push a baby out of my body.

428
00:22:09,502 --> 00:22:11,218
Isn't it interesting

429
00:22:11,242 --> 00:22:15,353
that the one and only request
we women would have of the men

430
00:22:15,377 --> 00:22:17,292
would be for them to leave?

431
00:22:21,296 --> 00:22:24,212
[All laughing]

432
00:22:30,914 --> 00:22:33,830
[Greta] Asking the men to leave
is not an option.

433
00:22:34,265 --> 00:22:35,310
Oh!

434
00:22:37,051 --> 00:22:39,334
I'd like you to imagine
Ruth and Cheryl.

435
00:22:39,358 --> 00:22:40,620
[Agata] No. Not again.

436
00:22:43,318 --> 00:22:44,493
[Ona] Please stop.

437
00:22:45,712 --> 00:22:48,212
Look. August is still
taking the minutes.

438
00:22:48,236 --> 00:22:49,996
[Laughter]

439
00:22:50,020 --> 00:22:53,415
I can't believe August
is still taking the minutes.

440
00:22:56,287 --> 00:22:57,787
[Autje] Sometimes I think
people laugh

441
00:22:57,811 --> 00:22:59,726
as hard as they'd like to cry.

442
00:23:02,903 --> 00:23:05,688
[Agata] August, you must think
we're all lunatics.

443
00:23:06,080 --> 00:23:08,101
I don't.

444
00:23:08,125 --> 00:23:10,737
And it doesn't matter
what I think, anyway.

445
00:23:11,868 --> 00:23:13,411
Is that true?

446
00:23:13,435 --> 00:23:15,515
Do you really think it doesn't
matter what you think?

447
00:23:19,136 --> 00:23:21,680
How would you feel
if in your entire life

448
00:23:21,704 --> 00:23:23,532
