528
00:28:46,725 --> 00:28:47,943
Ever again.

529
00:28:55,472 --> 00:28:56,580
[Autje] But...

530
00:28:56,604 --> 00:28:57,755
[Mejal] But what?

531
00:28:57,779 --> 00:29:00,018
[Autje] She doesn't
speak anymore.

532
00:29:00,042 --> 00:29:01,193
You all right?

533
00:29:01,217 --> 00:29:02,586
[Mejal] She speaks
to the children.

534
00:29:02,610 --> 00:29:04,501
[Girl] Kind of.

535
00:29:04,525 --> 00:29:06,285
I think they call her Melvin.

536
00:29:06,309 --> 00:29:07,484
[Children squeal]

537
00:29:10,313 --> 00:29:12,751
[Children speaking indistinctly]

538
00:29:26,329 --> 00:29:30,701
You know, during
the second world war in Italy,

539
00:29:30,725 --> 00:29:33,510
civilians would hide
in bomb shelters.

540
00:29:34,250 --> 00:29:35,706
Volunteers were needed

541
00:29:35,730 --> 00:29:38,777
to power the generators
that provided electricity.

542
00:29:40,126 --> 00:29:41,736
They rode bikes.

543
00:29:42,476 --> 00:29:44,106
[August chuckles]

544
00:29:44,130 --> 00:29:47,065
And when you were swinging
from the rafter earlier,

545
00:29:47,089 --> 00:29:50,590
I was, uh, reminded of this.

546
00:29:50,614 --> 00:29:52,616
You would have been
the perfect volunteer.

547
00:29:54,836 --> 00:29:56,490
If we were in a bomb shelter.

548
00:29:58,709 --> 00:30:01,166
Where would I ride the bike to
in such a small space?

549
00:30:01,190 --> 00:30:04,324
Oh, well, uh,
the bike would be stationary.

550
00:30:09,808 --> 00:30:11,505
I have to get the water
to the horses.

551
00:30:18,512 --> 00:30:19,774
Watch this.

552
00:30:27,303 --> 00:30:28,827
[August] Oh! [Chuckles]

553
00:30:32,091 --> 00:30:33,764
I'll bet you didn't learn
how to do things like that

554
00:30:33,788 --> 00:30:35,810
when you went to university.

555
00:30:35,834 --> 00:30:37,855
Only facts about
stationary bicycles

556
00:30:37,879 --> 00:30:39,359
in far off places.

557
00:30:41,927 --> 00:30:43,798
I suppose I shouldn't be
too sad then.

558
00:30:44,494 --> 00:30:45,931
That I won't ever go.

559
00:30:51,284 --> 00:30:53,871
Why were you forced
to leave the colony?

560
00:30:53,895 --> 00:30:55,854
My mother questioned things.

561
00:30:56,898 --> 00:30:58,291
She questioned god?

562
00:30:58,944 --> 00:31:00,312
Not god.

563
00:31:00,336 --> 00:31:01,381
Power.

564
00:31:02,469 --> 00:31:05,709
The rules made
in the name of god.

565
00:31:05,733 --> 00:31:09,408
And she encouraged others
to question things too.

566
00:31:09,432 --> 00:31:10,888
Like ona?

567
00:31:10,912 --> 00:31:11,913
Yes.

568
00:31:13,132 --> 00:31:14,916
Ona knew her well.

569
00:31:16,309 --> 00:31:17,745
Did she die?

570
00:31:29,888 --> 00:31:31,169
But sometimes,

571
00:31:31,193 --> 00:31:32,692
listening to you all
speaking today

572
00:31:32,716 --> 00:31:35,284
I can hear her so clearly.

573
00:31:38,113 --> 00:31:40,570
Why did the elders
let you come back?

574
00:31:40,594 --> 00:31:42,572
Well, I went to university

575
00:31:42,596 --> 00:31:46,121
so I could serve a purpose
and teach the boys.

576
00:31:47,079 --> 00:31:48,384
Too late.

577
00:32:02,137 --> 00:32:04,009
I want to help.

578
00:32:05,445 --> 00:32:06,925
And I don't know how.

579
00:32:08,491 --> 00:32:10,493
You came back for ona,
didn't you?

580
00:32:11,755 --> 00:32:13,496
The way you look at her is

581
00:32:14,758 --> 00:32:15,759
funny. [Chuckles softly]

582
00:32:17,196 --> 00:32:19,348
I don't know why
she won't just marry you.

583
00:32:19,372 --> 00:32:21,591
You both say so much
that doesn't make sense.

584
00:32:36,519 --> 00:32:38,478
[Mellow music
playing on speakers]

585
00:32:41,698 --> 00:32:43,352
[Boy] Mama.

586
00:32:46,051 --> 00:32:47,637
[Man on speaker]
All residents, please come out

587
00:32:47,661 --> 00:32:48,986
of your homes to be counted
for the 2010 census.

588
00:32:49,010 --> 00:32:51,162
Hey, hey, hey. Shoo, shoo, shoo!

589
00:32:51,186 --> 00:32:52,796
Away. Away!

590
00:32:55,974 --> 00:32:57,690
[Man] Please come out
and be counted now.

591
00:32:57,714 --> 00:32:59,040
Please come out of your homes

592
00:32:59,064 --> 00:33:01,109
to be counted
for the 2010 census.

593
00:33:08,987 --> 00:33:10,945
[Mellow music continues
on speakers]

594
00:33:15,167 --> 00:33:17,406
All residents must come out
of their homes

595
00:33:17,430 --> 00:33:20,041
to be counted
for the 2010 census.

596
00:33:26,961 --> 00:33:28,006
[Girl grunts]

597
00:33:28,484 --> 00:33:29,529
Whoo!

598
00:33:38,364 --> 00:33:41,019
All right.
You want to try this one?

599
00:33:44,500 --> 00:33:46,043
[Man] This is the 2010 census.

600
00:33:46,067 --> 00:33:47,392
Please come out of your homes

601
00:33:47,416 --> 00:33:49,549
to be counted
for the 2010 census.

602
00:33:55,468 --> 00:33:57,209
- Tickle, tickle, tickle.
- [Laughing]

603
00:34:10,526 --> 00:34:13,462
[Man] I'm here to collect data
for the 2010 census.

604
00:34:13,486 --> 00:34:15,072
Please come out
of your homes now

605
00:34:15,096 --> 00:34:16,271
to be counted.

606
00:34:20,014 --> 00:34:21,078
[Neitje] Let's go.

607
00:34:21,102 --> 00:34:22,340
Why?

608
00:34:22,364 --> 00:34:23,800
Let's just... let's go.

609
00:34:25,193 --> 00:34:27,021
[Both giggling]

610
00:34:40,600 --> 00:34:42,056
The ladies standing
in front of me.

611
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:44,101
- [All laughing]
- How old are you?

612
00:34:44,125 --> 00:34:46,016
- I'm 15.
- I'm 16.

613
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:48,105
Okay.
So you must have boyfriends.

614
00:34:48,129 --> 00:34:49,498
Oh!

615
00:34:49,522 --> 00:34:51,362
- No. We don't have boyfriends.
- No boyfriend?

616
00:34:53,743 --> 00:34:55,112
[Man] I'll see you ladies again.

617
00:34:55,136 --> 00:34:56,572
Mm-hmm - [man] Take care.

618
00:35:07,192 --> 00:35:12,303
[August singing]
♪ homecoming queen ♪

619
00:35:12,327 --> 00:35:16,133
♪ cheer up, sleepy Jean ♪

620
00:35:16,157 --> 00:35:19,136
♪ oh, what can it mean ♪

621
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:22,792
♪ to a daydream believer ♪

622
00:35:22,816 --> 00:35:25,229
♪ and a home... ♪

623
00:35:25,253 --> 00:35:26,559
[Chirping]

624
00:35:57,024 --> 00:35:58,025
Where is autje?

625
00:35:59,548 --> 00:36:01,855
[Agata] Well, we must
begin without her.

626
00:36:05,206 --> 00:36:06,206
Thank you.

627
00:36:07,991 --> 00:36:09,621
Were you smoking?

628
00:36:09,645 --> 00:36:10,883
Is that any of your business?

629
00:36:10,907 --> 00:36:12,126
Please.

630
00:36:13,997 --> 00:36:15,390
[Autje sobbing]

631
00:36:16,739 --> 00:36:19,457
[Autje] I can't live
a second longer!

632
00:36:19,481 --> 00:36:20,763
[Mariche] Autje!

633
00:36:20,787 --> 00:36:22,504
[All screaming]

634
00:36:22,528 --> 00:36:24,138
[Gasping]

635
00:36:27,141 --> 00:36:28,597
- [Women] Autje!
- [All sigh in relief]

636
00:36:28,621 --> 00:36:30,013
[Women laughing]

637
00:36:32,102 --> 00:36:33,713
Autje, wait until
I get ahold of you.

638
00:36:35,105 --> 00:36:36,648
The census taker just told us

639
00:36:36,672 --> 00:36:37,736
that one of our men is returning

640
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:40,478
from the city late tonight.

641
00:36:40,502 --> 00:36:42,437
They need more bail money
for the attackers.

642
00:36:42,461 --> 00:36:43,525
Which man?

643
00:36:43,549 --> 00:36:45,048
[Suspenseful music playing]

644
00:36:45,072 --> 00:36:46,160
Your klaas.

645
00:36:47,335 --> 00:36:49,226
[Agata] So time
is of the essence.

646
00:36:49,250 --> 00:36:50,947
Everyone get back to your seats.

647
00:36:54,212 --> 00:36:56,562
[Greta] August, please,
pros for leaving.

648
00:36:57,650 --> 00:36:59,173
Pros for leaving.

649
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:04,023
[Mejal] We will be gone.

650
00:37:04,047 --> 00:37:05,416
[Greta] We will be safe.

651
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:06,678
Maybe not.

652
00:37:06,702 --> 00:37:08,071
The first is most
definitely a fact,

653
00:37:08,095 --> 00:37:09,638
that if we leave
we will be gone.

654
00:37:09,662 --> 00:37:11,838
Do we really need to state
the obvious over and over?

655
00:37:13,492 --> 00:37:14,667
[Agata] Yes, autje.

656
00:37:15,929 --> 00:37:18,473
We will see a bit of the world.

657
00:37:18,497 --> 00:37:19,996
[August] Let's move on
to the cons of leaving.

658
00:37:20,020 --> 00:37:21,127
We, the women, will decide

659
00:37:21,151 --> 00:37:23,023
what happens in these meetings.

660
00:37:24,242 --> 00:37:26,872
Not a two-bit failed farmer
who must teach.

661
00:37:26,896 --> 00:37:28,613
You have been invited here.

662
00:37:28,637 --> 00:37:30,267
You have been invited
here to listen

663
00:37:30,291 --> 00:37:32,835
to what we have to say
and write it down.

664
00:37:32,859 --> 00:37:35,707
Nothing more. Just listen.

665
00:37:35,731 --> 00:37:37,318
Mariche!

666
00:37:37,342 --> 00:37:40,886
Klaas will be returning soon
and you are wasting time.

667
00:37:40,910 --> 00:37:42,888
He will come to your house
just long enough

668
00:37:42,912 --> 00:37:46,370
to take his animals in order
to sell for bail money

669
00:37:46,394 --> 00:37:49,373
that will see the rapists
return to the colony

670
00:37:49,397 --> 00:37:50,809
and he will lay his hands

671
00:37:50,833 --> 00:37:53,595
on you and on your children.

672
00:37:53,619 --> 00:37:56,511
And you, as always, do nothing,

673
00:37:56,535 --> 00:37:59,775
but fire away at us
with all of this rage.

674
00:37:59,799 --> 00:38:00,843
[Suspenseful music stops]

675
00:38:02,105 --> 00:38:03,518
I would like to apologize

676
00:38:03,542 --> 00:38:05,761
for wrongly attempting
to nudge the proceedings.

677
00:38:07,546 --> 00:38:09,025
That's not my place.

678
00:38:09,852 --> 00:38:11,332
[Laughing]

679
00:38:14,161 --> 00:38:15,380
[Greta] Mejal!

680
00:38:18,992 --> 00:38:20,123
[Clears throat]

681
00:38:20,733 --> 00:38:21,908
I'll stop.

682
00:38:23,344 --> 00:38:24,780
[Miep] Mama.

683
00:38:29,350 --> 00:38:31,657
What's the matter?
What's the matter?

684
00:38:33,049 --> 00:38:34,573
What is it? Hmm?

685
00:38:38,185 --> 00:38:39,926
Miep, what is it?

686
00:38:41,014 --> 00:38:42,798
[Miep] I hurt.

687
00:38:45,888 --> 00:38:47,194
It's all right.

688
00:38:49,631 --> 00:38:50,980
It's all right.

689
00:38:57,770 --> 00:38:59,075
It's all right.

690
00:39:06,039 --> 00:39:08,215
There are no cons of leaving.

691
00:39:10,391 --> 00:39:12,045
It's all right.

692
00:39:16,223 --> 00:39:18,268
Not to worry, nettie.

693
00:39:25,406 --> 00:39:29,541
[Singing] ♪ children of
the heavenly father ♪

694
00:39:30,933 --> 00:39:36,175
♪ safely in his bosom gather ♪

695
00:39:36,199 --> 00:39:41,311
♪ nestling bird
nor star in heaven ♪

696
00:39:41,335 --> 00:39:44,009
♪ such a refuge ♪

697
00:39:44,033 --> 00:39:47,317
♪ e'er was given ♪

698
00:39:47,341 --> 00:39:52,409
♪ though he giveth
or he taketh ♪

699
00:39:52,433 --> 00:39:57,414
♪ god his children
ne'er forsaketh ♪

700
00:39:57,438 --> 00:40:02,114
♪ his, the loving purpose
solely ♪

701
00:40:02,138 --> 00:40:04,595
♪ to preserve them ♪

702
00:40:04,619 --> 00:40:08,512
♪ pure and holy ♪

703
00:40:08,536 --> 00:40:13,952
♪ children of
the heavenly father ♪

704
00:40:13,976 --> 00:40:15,737
♪ safely in ♪

705
00:40:15,761 --> 00:40:19,305
♪ his bosom gather ♪

706
00:40:19,329 --> 00:40:24,441
♪ nestling bird
nor star in heaven ♪

707
00:40:24,465 --> 00:40:27,183
♪ such a refuge ♪

708
00:40:27,207 --> 00:40:30,969
♪ e'er was given ♪

709
00:40:30,993 --> 00:40:32,299
[Melancholic music playing]

710
00:40:34,301 --> 00:40:35,931
If we do leave the colony,

711
00:40:35,955 --> 00:40:38,412
how will we live with the pain
of never seeing our brothers

712
00:40:38,436 --> 00:40:39,915
and our sons again?

713
00:40:41,177 --> 00:40:42,352
The men?

714
00:40:57,542 --> 00:40:58,542
[Greta] Time will heal.

715
00:41:01,067 --> 00:41:05,090
Our freedom and safety
are the ultimate goals.

716
00:41:05,114 --> 00:41:08,466
And it is men who prevent us
from achieving those goals.

717
00:41:10,990 --> 00:41:12,470
[Mariche] But not all men.

718
00:41:27,920 --> 00:41:30,464
[Ona] Perhaps not men,

719
00:41:30,488 --> 00:41:32,335
but a way of seeing the world,
and us women,

720
00:41:32,359 --> 00:41:33,641
which has been allowed
to take hold

721
00:41:33,665 --> 00:41:35,623
of men's hearts and minds.

722
00:41:38,713 --> 00:41:41,170
[Neitje] So if we leave...
If we leave

723
00:41:41,194 --> 00:41:43,283
I will never see
my brothers again?

724
00:41:44,980 --> 00:41:46,504
[Autje] Who will
take care of them?

725
00:41:47,635 --> 00:41:48,897
Of them all?

726
00:41:50,333 --> 00:41:52,355
[Greta] We can't know
if we will stay or leave

727
00:41:52,379 --> 00:41:53,835
before we resolve

728
00:41:53,859 --> 00:41:56,339
these last-minute concerns.

729
00:41:57,819 --> 00:41:59,971
I wouldn't call
the future of our relationship

730
00:41:59,995 --> 00:42:02,737
with the boys and men we love
"last-minute concerns."

731
00:42:28,981 --> 00:42:30,199
There we go.

732
00:42:41,036 --> 00:42:43,885
[Children chattering]

733
00:42:43,909 --> 00:42:48,585
[Autje] It was all waiting
to happen before it happened.

734
00:42:48,609 --> 00:42:50,500
You could look back
and follow the breadcrumbs

735
00:42:50,524 --> 00:42:52,831
along the path
that led to violence.

736
00:42:53,701 --> 00:42:55,592
When we looked back,

737
00:42:55,616 --> 00:42:58,334
we could see
that it had been everywhere,

738
00:42:58,358 --> 00:43:00,403
whether it was happening yet
or not.

739
00:43:01,361 --> 00:43:03,581
[Girl] Hi. [Exclaims excitedly]

740
00:43:04,886 --> 00:43:06,366
[Children speaking indistinctly]

741
00:43:16,071 --> 00:43:17,290
[Miep] Hi.

742
00:43:22,338 --> 00:43:24,036
[Heaving]

743
00:43:30,999 --> 00:43:32,610
I'll get you some water.

744
00:43:40,966 --> 00:43:42,010
[Melancholic music fades]

745
00:43:44,056 --> 00:43:45,797
There's no cup or anything.

746
00:43:49,539 --> 00:43:50,584
[Slurps]

747
00:43:55,241 --> 00:43:56,372
[Water splashes]

748
00:43:58,113 --> 00:43:59,158
[Slurps]

749
00:44:04,729 --> 00:44:05,860
[Ona sighs]

750
00:44:16,305 --> 00:44:18,351
It's good
that you're here, August.

751
00:44:20,179 --> 00:44:22,355
To remind us of what's possible.

752
00:44:24,226 --> 00:44:25,967
Because it's easy to forget.

753
00:44:34,846 --> 00:44:36,040
I'm so sorry, ona.

754
00:44:36,064 --> 00:44:37,370
[Chuckles]

755
00:44:39,764 --> 00:44:40,915
One day I'd like to hear that

756
00:44:40,939 --> 00:44:42,767
from someone
who should be saying it.

757
00:44:55,736 --> 00:44:57,129
Why does love...

758
00:44:58,217 --> 00:45:00,543
The absence of love,
the end of love,

759
00:45:00,567 --> 00:45:02,090
the need for love,

760
00:45:03,048 --> 00:45:05,224
result in so much violence?

761
00:45:11,621 --> 00:45:12,622
Ona.

762
00:45:14,799 --> 00:45:15,799
Ona.

763
00:45:18,454 --> 00:45:20,282
I could take care of you

764
00:45:20,848 --> 00:45:22,154
and your child.

765
00:45:25,592 --> 00:45:26,593
I would like to.

766
00:45:30,728 --> 00:45:31,792
I, um...

767
00:45:31,816 --> 00:45:33,750
I know,

768
00:45:33,774 --> 00:45:35,174
but you don't have
to say the words.

769
00:45:38,170 --> 00:45:40,912
If I were married,
I wouldn't be myself.

770
00:45:41,956 --> 00:45:43,717
So the person you love
would be gone.

771
00:45:43,741 --> 00:45:44,829
[Chuckles]

772
00:45:53,533 --> 00:45:54,534
[Ona chuckles]

773
00:45:56,362 --> 00:45:57,798
Your child...

774
00:45:59,234 --> 00:46:00,235
[August chuckles]

775
00:46:01,410 --> 00:46:02,605
If we stay
and we don't win the fight,

776
00:46:02,629 --> 00:46:04,413
my child will be given

777
00:46:05,371 --> 00:46:07,112
to another family here.

778
00:46:08,722 --> 00:46:10,898
Maybe even the family
of my attacker.

779
00:46:13,335 --> 00:46:15,250
If we stay
and don't win the fight.

780
00:46:19,515 --> 00:46:21,387
You won't let that happen. No.

781
00:46:21,953 --> 00:46:22,954
No.

782
00:46:24,869 --> 00:46:26,131
No, I won't.

783
00:46:45,672 --> 00:46:47,476
[Inhales deeply]

784
00:46:47,500 --> 00:46:49,826
[Greta] August,
we need to discuss options

785
00:46:49,850 --> 00:46:51,349
for the men and the older boys,

786
00:46:51,373 --> 00:46:52,829
if the women decide to leave.

787
00:46:52,853 --> 00:46:54,700
Which is a waste of time
because we're not leaving.

788
00:46:54,724 --> 00:46:56,572
The men should leave with us
if they wish.

789
00:46:56,596 --> 00:46:58,313
Then what on earth
is the point of us leaving?

790
00:46:58,337 --> 00:47:00,271
Well, they could be allowed
to join the women later

791
00:47:00,295 --> 00:47:02,143
once the women
have established themselves

792
00:47:02,167 --> 00:47:03,927
and are thriving.

793
00:47:03,951 --> 00:47:05,407
Should we add

794
00:47:05,431 --> 00:47:08,584
"thriving as a collective,
literate community"?

795
00:47:08,608 --> 00:47:10,281
Literate's your word. Not ours.

796
00:47:10,305 --> 00:47:11,761
We don't need your university
language to make our plans.

797
00:47:11,785 --> 00:47:13,502
Put it in.
We know what it means.

798
00:47:13,526 --> 00:47:14,938
Continue, Greta.

799
00:47:14,962 --> 00:47:17,201
Young boys,
simple-minded boys of any age,

800
00:47:17,225 --> 00:47:19,682
Cornelius who's confined
to a wheelchair,

801
00:47:19,706 --> 00:47:20,857
will accompany the women.

802
00:47:20,881 --> 00:47:22,772
I vote for the first option.

803
00:47:22,796 --> 00:47:24,382
The men should leave with us
if they wish.

804
00:47:24,406 --> 00:47:25,644
The first option is ridiculous

805
00:47:25,668 --> 00:47:27,298
and should be
crossed off the list.

806
00:47:27,322 --> 00:47:28,386
[Mariche] Why are some ideas
written down and considered,

807
00:47:28,410 --> 00:47:30,325
and others crossed out?

808
00:47:30,804 --> 00:47:32,086
[Sighs]

809
00:47:32,110 --> 00:47:34,697
I want to leave.
I'd like to strangle myself.

810
00:47:34,721 --> 00:47:35,872
Mariche, it's possible
that all the men

811
00:47:35,896 --> 00:47:37,352
would choose to leave with us.

812
00:47:37,376 --> 00:47:39,354
And then all we'd be doing
is recreating our colony

813
00:47:39,378 --> 00:47:40,790
with all of its
dangers elsewhere.

814
00:47:40,814 --> 00:47:41,922
[Agata] And the men
would definitely

815
00:47:41,946 --> 00:47:43,271
leave with us because

816
00:47:43,295 --> 00:47:44,663
they can't survive without us.

817
00:47:44,687 --> 00:47:45,926
Well, not for longer
than a day or two.

818
00:47:45,950 --> 00:47:47,144
[Salome] We have not
decided to leave.

819
00:47:47,168 --> 00:47:48,711
I'd like to remind everyone
of that.

820
00:47:48,735 --> 00:47:50,495
[Agata] And how can we leave
at all if we've never

821
00:47:50,519 --> 00:47:52,933
been allowed to even see
a map of the world?

822
00:47:52,957 --> 00:47:55,587
[August] I can secure
a world map for you.

823
00:47:55,611 --> 00:47:59,461
I also have a, um,
map of this specific region.

824
00:47:59,485 --> 00:48:01,028
Well, that will do.

825
00:48:01,052 --> 00:48:03,421
It's not like we are planning
to travel the planet.

826
00:48:03,445 --> 00:48:04,988
[Ona] Perhaps we are.

827
00:48:05,012 --> 00:48:06,337
Did you know
that the migration period

828
00:48:06,361 --> 00:48:08,644
for butterflies
and dragonflies is so long

829
00:48:08,668 --> 00:48:10,167
that it's often
only the grandchildren

830
00:48:10,191 --> 00:48:12,498
that arrive
at the intended destination?

831
00:48:14,239 --> 00:48:15,805
Yes. So, it...

832
00:48:17,938 --> 00:48:19,350
Yes.

833
00:48:19,374 --> 00:48:21,352
Perhaps, if we went beyond
where the map showed us,

834
00:48:21,376 --> 00:48:24,051
we could create
our own map as we go.

835
00:48:24,075 --> 00:48:26,033
So now you want to leave, ona?

836
00:48:28,993 --> 00:48:31,754
[Breathing heavily]

837
00:48:31,778 --> 00:48:33,649
[Agata] Are you all right,
mejal?

838
00:48:36,957 --> 00:48:39,327
Nope. She's having
one of her episodes.

839
00:48:39,351 --> 00:48:41,329
[Mejal gasping]

840
00:48:41,353 --> 00:48:43,200
[Agata] Father almighty,

841
00:48:43,224 --> 00:48:45,942
in all humility
and supplication we ask thee

842
00:48:45,966 --> 00:48:47,489
for thy abundant kindness

843
00:48:48,055 --> 00:48:49,380
at this moment.

844
00:48:49,404 --> 00:48:51,513
We beseech thee

845
00:48:51,537 --> 00:48:54,951
to have mercy
on our sister mejal.

846
00:48:54,975 --> 00:48:57,388
- [Screaming]
- Please, in your beneficence,

847
00:48:57,412 --> 00:48:59,173
heal her.

848
00:48:59,197 --> 00:49:01,349
- And please...
- [Inaudible]

849
00:49:01,373 --> 00:49:04,656
We ask of thee, envelop her

850
00:49:04,680 --> 00:49:07,485
in your strength
and everlasting love,

851
00:49:07,509 --> 00:49:09,139
and please drive out
the sickness

852
00:49:09,163 --> 00:49:11,035
which afflicts her now.

853
00:49:12,558 --> 00:49:13,951
[Mejal sobs and exhales]

854
00:49:16,562 --> 00:49:18,433
[Mejal breathing heavily]

855
00:49:28,530 --> 00:49:29,943
[Weakly] Help me up.

856
00:49:29,967 --> 00:49:31,925
[Agata sighs in relief]
Praise be to god.

857
00:49:36,147 --> 00:49:37,515
Why is it
only mejal has these...?

858
00:49:37,539 --> 00:49:38,690
Be quiet.

859
00:49:38,714 --> 00:49:39,889
We were all attacked.

860
00:49:40,847 --> 00:49:41,955
Not all of us need to draw

861
00:49:41,979 --> 00:49:43,676
so much attention to ourselves.

862
00:49:44,982 --> 00:49:46,548
[Laughing]

863
00:49:47,419 --> 00:49:49,005
What attention?

864
00:49:49,029 --> 00:49:50,180
I speak less
than all of you put together.

865
00:49:50,204 --> 00:49:51,355
How have I offended you?

866
00:49:51,379 --> 00:49:53,357
[Mariche] You have
these attacks.

867
00:49:53,381 --> 00:49:55,620
You smoke.

868
00:49:55,644 --> 00:49:59,189
Why? Why is it so much
harder for you than for us?

869
00:49:59,213 --> 00:50:01,322
We were all attacked. All of us.

870
00:50:01,346 --> 00:50:04,978
We are wasting our time
by passing this burden,

871
00:50:05,002 --> 00:50:07,154
this sack of stones,
from one to the next,

872
00:50:07,178 --> 00:50:10,070
by pushing our pain away.

873
00:50:10,094 --> 00:50:13,377
Let's absorb it ourselves.
Let's inhale it.

874
00:50:13,401 --> 00:50:14,489
Let's digest it.

875
00:50:15,273 --> 00:50:17,797
Let's process it into fuel.

876
00:50:23,368 --> 00:50:24,891
Speak, mejal.

877
00:50:25,631 --> 00:50:26,936
We are listening.

878
00:50:31,028 --> 00:50:33,160
They made us
disbelieve ourselves.

879
00:50:38,600 --> 00:50:41,473
That was worse than...

880
00:50:42,430 --> 00:50:43,431
[Gasping]

881
00:50:44,824 --> 00:50:46,043
[Salome] Mejal.

882
00:50:54,703 --> 00:50:55,767
[Ona] Klaas, when he returns,

883
00:50:55,791 --> 00:50:57,378
may take horses or livestock

884
00:50:57,402 --> 00:50:58,640
that we would need
along the way.

885
00:50:58,664 --> 00:51:00,207
[Salome] Along the way?

886
00:51:00,231 --> 00:51:01,536
We're not leaving.

887
00:51:05,018 --> 00:51:06,952
You are changing your mind, ona.

888
00:51:06,976 --> 00:51:09,240
I don't believe
that's a sin, is it?

889
00:51:11,155 --> 00:51:13,829
[Mariche] How will
we be forgiven for all this?

890
00:51:13,853 --> 00:51:15,961
How will we be forgiven,

891
00:51:15,985 --> 00:51:18,703
if not by the elders
whom we have disobeyed?

892
00:51:18,727 --> 00:51:22,011
Perhaps there will be
other elders or men of god

893
00:51:22,035 --> 00:51:23,795
who will be able
to forgive our sins.

894
00:51:23,819 --> 00:51:26,450
We do not need to be forgiven
by the men of god

895
00:51:26,474 --> 00:51:27,799
for protecting our children

896
00:51:27,823 --> 00:51:29,149
from the depraved actions
of vicious men

897
00:51:29,173 --> 00:51:30,411
who are often the very same men

898
00:51:30,435 --> 00:51:32,350
we're meant to ask
for forgiveness!

899
00:51:34,178 --> 00:51:36,634
If god is a loving god then...

900
00:51:36,658 --> 00:51:38,225
He will forgive us himself.

901
00:51:39,574 --> 00:51:40,769
If god is a vengeful god

902
00:51:40,793 --> 00:51:42,751
then he has created us
in his image.

903
00:51:44,623 --> 00:51:46,818
If god is omnipotent,

904
00:51:46,842 --> 00:51:48,516
then why has he not protected

905
00:51:48,540 --> 00:51:50,803
the women and girls
of this colony?

906
00:51:55,982 --> 00:51:58,221
I will destroy

907
00:51:58,245 --> 00:52:02,075
any living thing
that harms my child.

908
00:52:04,991 --> 00:52:07,298
I will tear it limb from limb.

909
00:52:08,168 --> 00:52:10,146
I will desecrate its body

910
00:52:10,170 --> 00:52:12,172
and I will Bury it alive.

911
00:52:13,478 --> 00:52:14,933
I will challenge god on the spot

912
00:52:14,957 --> 00:52:16,109
to strike me dead

913
00:52:16,133 --> 00:52:17,284
if I have sinned

914
00:52:17,308 --> 00:52:19,721
by protecting my child
from evil,

915
00:52:19,745 --> 00:52:22,835
and by destroying that evil
that it may not harm another!

916
00:52:23,792 --> 00:52:25,533
I will lie,

917
00:52:26,708 --> 00:52:28,773
I will hunt, I will kill.

918
00:52:28,797 --> 00:52:30,471
I will dance on graves

919
00:52:30,495 --> 00:52:33,082
and I will burn forever in hell

920
00:52:33,106 --> 00:52:35,215
before I allow another man

921
00:52:35,239 --> 00:52:37,042
to satisfy his violent urges

922
00:52:37,066 --> 00:52:39,982
with the body
of my four-year-old child!

923
00:52:40,505 --> 00:52:41,680
[Sobbing]

924
00:52:48,948 --> 00:52:50,558
[Emotional music playing]

925
00:53:08,620 --> 00:53:11,449
I suggest we think
about what is good.

926
00:53:13,712 --> 00:53:15,279
"Whatever is true,

927
00:53:16,280 --> 00:53:18,107
"whatever is honorable,

928
00:53:19,108 --> 00:53:20,719
"whatever is just,

929
00:53:21,633 --> 00:53:23,350
"whatever is pure,

930
00:53:23,374 --> 00:53:25,743
"whatever is pleasing,

931
00:53:25,767 --> 00:53:27,639
"whatever is commendable,

932
00:53:28,466 --> 00:53:30,705
"if there is any excellence

933
00:53:30,729 --> 00:53:34,056
"and if there
is anything worthy of praise,

934
00:53:34,080 --> 00:53:36,841
"think about these things

935
00:53:36,865 --> 00:53:40,173
"and the peace of god
be with you."

936
00:53:42,306 --> 00:53:44,525
I will become a murderer
if I stay.

937
00:53:56,363 --> 00:53:58,235
[Emotional music continues]

938
00:54:08,767 --> 00:54:10,247
[Sniffles]

939
00:54:15,469 --> 00:54:16,731
[Ona clears throat]

940
00:54:21,345 --> 00:54:23,410
[Ona] I know what these are.
These are letters.

941
00:54:23,434 --> 00:54:25,238
But what are these?

942
00:54:25,262 --> 00:54:27,979
[August] They're commas.

943
00:54:28,003 --> 00:54:31,529
They signify a short pause,
or a breath in the text.

944
00:54:35,141 --> 00:54:37,186
There's also a butterfly
called a comma.

945
00:54:38,449 --> 00:54:40,146
- Is that so?
- Mm-hmm.

946
00:55:00,166 --> 00:55:01,846
- [Agata] Salome.
- [Emotional music fades]

947
00:55:03,735 --> 00:55:07,541
If you will become a murderer
by staying here in the colony,

948
00:55:07,565 --> 00:55:09,064
side by side with the men

949
00:55:09,088 --> 00:55:11,351
who are responsible
for the attacks,

950
00:55:12,396 --> 00:55:13,614
then you must,

951
00:55:15,573 --> 00:55:17,357
to protect your own soul,

952
00:55:18,053 --> 00:55:19,751
leave the colony.

953
00:55:21,013 --> 00:55:22,599
We are not all murderers.

954
00:55:22,623 --> 00:55:23,905
Not yet.

955
00:55:23,929 --> 00:55:25,254
[Agata] I have done
what the verse

956
00:55:25,278 --> 00:55:26,821
from philippians instructed,

957
00:55:26,845 --> 00:55:29,195
which is to think
about what is good,

958
00:55:30,152 --> 00:55:32,174
what is just, what is pure,

959
00:55:32,198 --> 00:55:33,547
what is excellent.

960
00:55:35,114 --> 00:55:36,463
Pacifism.

961
00:55:39,205 --> 00:55:40,922
Pacifism is good.

962
00:55:40,946 --> 00:55:42,164
Any violence

963
00:55:42,904 --> 00:55:44,515
is unjustifiable.

964
00:55:45,429 --> 00:55:49,670
By staying here, we women

965
00:55:49,694 --> 00:55:52,412
will be betraying
the central tenet of our faith

966
00:55:52,436 --> 00:55:53,828
which is pacifism,

967
00:55:56,004 --> 00:55:57,615
because by staying

968
00:55:59,921 --> 00:56:03,229
we will knowingly
be placing ourselves

969
00:56:04,535 --> 00:56:08,452
in a direct collision course
with violence,

970
00:56:10,149 --> 00:56:13,065
either by us or against us.

971
00:56:14,675 --> 00:56:19,071
This colony is the only home
I've ever known.

972
00:56:21,290 --> 00:56:23,249
And I don't want to leave.

973
00:56:23,945 --> 00:56:25,338
But by staying,

974
00:56:26,165 --> 00:56:27,993
we'll be inviting harm.

975
00:56:29,255 --> 00:56:31,233
We will be in a state of war.

976
00:56:31,257 --> 00:56:35,043
We will turn this colony
into a battlefield.

977
00:56:38,699 --> 00:56:40,938
[Ona] We cannot
become murderers.

978
00:56:40,962 --> 00:56:43,487
And we cannot endure
any more violence,

979
00:56:45,706 --> 00:56:47,404
which is why we must leave.

980
00:57:09,643 --> 00:57:10,664
I've also been thinking

981
00:57:10,688 --> 00:57:13,623
about the verse from philippians

982
00:57:13,647 --> 00:57:15,867
and I've been thinking
about what is good.

983
00:57:17,259 --> 00:57:18,696
Freedom is good.

984
00:57:19,740 --> 00:57:21,786
It is better than slavery.

985
00:57:23,048 --> 00:57:24,789
Forgiveness is good.

986
00:57:25,790 --> 00:57:27,487
It's better than revenge.

987
00:57:28,706 --> 00:57:31,989
And hope for the unknown
is good,

988
00:57:32,013 --> 00:57:34,557
it is better than
hatred of the familiar.

989
00:57:34,581 --> 00:57:36,627
And what about security,

990
00:57:37,628 --> 00:57:40,544
and safety, and home,
and family?

991
00:57:41,675 --> 00:57:44,591
What about marriage,

992
00:57:46,724 --> 00:57:50,094
and love, ona?

993
00:57:50,118 --> 00:57:52,575
[Ona] I don't know
about those things,

994
00:57:52,599 --> 00:57:54,035
any of them.

995
00:57:55,036 --> 00:57:56,734
Except for love

996
00:57:57,778 --> 00:58:00,302
and... even love
is mysterious to me.

997
00:58:01,216 --> 00:58:02,542
And I believe that my home

998
00:58:02,566 --> 00:58:04,108
is with my mother,
and my sister,

999
00:58:04,132 --> 00:58:06,657
and my unborn child,
wherever that may be.

1000
00:58:09,050 --> 00:58:11,183
Will you not hate that child?

1001
00:58:14,403 --> 00:58:15,816
That child's the child of a man

1002
00:58:15,840 --> 00:58:17,581
who inspires
violent thoughts in you.

1003
00:58:22,673 --> 00:58:25,240
I already love this child
more than anything.

1004
00:58:26,590 --> 00:58:28,568
He or she
is as innocent and lovable

1005
00:58:28,592 --> 00:58:30,091
as the evening sun.

1006
00:58:30,115 --> 00:58:33,248
So too was the child's father
when he was born.

1007
00:58:37,514 --> 00:58:38,752
[Mariche] But, if you're saying

1008
00:58:38,776 --> 00:58:41,648
that forgiveness
is better than revenge...

1009
00:58:43,781 --> 00:58:46,368
Aren't you saying
that we must stay here

1010
00:58:46,392 --> 00:58:47,761
and forgive the men?

1011
00:58:47,785 --> 00:58:50,831
We cannot forgive
because we are forced to.

1012
00:58:53,399 --> 00:58:58,056
But, with some distance
perhaps I am able

1013
00:58:59,927 --> 00:59:03,017
to understand how these crimes
may have occurred.

1014
00:59:04,410 --> 00:59:06,214
And with that distance,

1015
00:59:06,238 --> 00:59:08,719
maybe I am able
to pity these men,

1016
00:59:10,459 --> 00:59:12,331
perhaps forgive them.

1017
00:59:13,245 --> 00:59:15,029
And even love them.

1018
00:59:17,379 --> 00:59:19,773
Not fighting. But moving.

1019
00:59:20,687 --> 00:59:26,408
Always moving. Never fighting.
Just moving.

1020
00:59:26,432 --> 00:59:29,933
Never fighting. Just moving.
Never fighting. Always moving.

1021
00:59:29,957 --> 00:59:31,587
Would you snap out of it?

1022
00:59:31,611 --> 00:59:32,719
[Salome] You snap out of it.

1023
00:59:32,743 --> 00:59:34,068
[Mejal] All of you
snap out of it.

1024
00:59:34,092 --> 00:59:36,181
Have you lost your minds?
The sun is gone.

1025
00:59:39,227 --> 00:59:42,404
I want to tell another story
about Ruth and Cheryl.

1026
00:59:47,932 --> 00:59:49,213
[Chuckles softly]

1027
00:59:49,237 --> 00:59:50,543
[Mellow music playing]

1028
00:59:51,326 --> 00:59:52,695
I was always frightened

1029
00:59:52,719 --> 00:59:55,548
of the northern road
out of the colony.

1030
00:59:57,637 --> 01:00:00,205
There are so many gullies
on either side of the road.

1031
01:00:03,991 --> 01:00:07,623
The buggy used to lurch
side to side.

1032
01:00:07,647 --> 01:00:09,364
Ruth and Cheryl were simply

1033
01:00:09,388 --> 01:00:11,433
following my commands
of the reins,

1034
01:00:12,609 --> 01:00:15,239
but, they were
jerky and frenetic.

1035
01:00:15,263 --> 01:00:17,352
And it was dangerous.

1036
01:00:19,616 --> 01:00:22,420
It was only when I learned
to focus my gaze

1037
01:00:22,444 --> 01:00:25,075
far down ahead of me

1038
01:00:25,099 --> 01:00:26,555
and not on the road

1039
01:00:26,579 --> 01:00:28,688
immediately in front
of Ruth and Cheryl,

1040
01:00:28,712 --> 01:00:30,888
that I started to feel safe.

1041
01:00:31,932 --> 01:00:34,718
[Breathing heavily]

1042
01:00:39,897 --> 01:00:41,962
Leaving will give us

1043
01:00:41,986 --> 01:00:44,858
the more farseeing perspective
we need

1044
01:00:45,642 --> 01:00:47,034
to forgive.

1045
01:00:51,648 --> 01:00:55,410
Which is to love properly

1046
01:00:55,434 --> 01:00:58,785
and keep the peace,
according to our faith.

1047
01:01:00,352 --> 01:01:01,721
Therefore, our leaving

1048
01:01:01,745 --> 01:01:04,462
wouldn't be an act of cowardice

1049
01:01:04,486 --> 01:01:05,725
or abandonment.

1050
01:01:05,749 --> 01:01:06,813
Let's see you go.

1051
01:01:06,837 --> 01:01:08,118
It wouldn't be because

1052
01:01:08,142 --> 01:01:12,122
we were excommunicated
or exiled.

1053
01:01:12,146 --> 01:01:15,038
It would be
a supreme act of faith...

1054
01:01:15,062 --> 01:01:16,692
Come on, let's go. Let's go.

1055
01:01:16,716 --> 01:01:20,764
A step towards
love and forgiveness.

1056
01:01:25,029 --> 01:01:28,554
Leaving is how
we demonstrate our faith.

1057
01:01:30,295 --> 01:01:31,620
We are leaving because

1058
01:01:31,644 --> 01:01:34,821
our faith is stronger
than the rules.

1059
01:01:38,738 --> 01:01:40,392
Bigger than our life.

1060
01:01:52,796 --> 01:01:54,449
[Mellow music fades]

1061
01:02:04,372 --> 01:02:06,679
I'm sorry.
But I think I might be dying.

1062
01:02:12,816 --> 01:02:15,664
Mother, you're not dying.

1063
01:02:15,688 --> 01:02:17,734
Your glasses need cleaning.

1064
01:02:18,822 --> 01:02:20,737
[Laughing]

1065
01:02:23,391 --> 01:02:25,524
Why are you laughing?

1066
01:02:26,960 --> 01:02:28,919
We cannot leave.

1067
01:02:29,528 --> 01:02:31,462
We...

1068
01:02:31,486 --> 01:02:34,248
It would be better
to stay and fight than leave.

1069
01:02:34,272 --> 01:02:35,684
Do you really mean
that you want to stay

1070
01:02:35,708 --> 01:02:37,991
and not fight?

1071
01:02:38,015 --> 01:02:39,949
Because when was the last time
you had the strength

1072
01:02:39,973 --> 01:02:41,821
to stand up
to the aggression of klaas,

1073
01:02:41,845 --> 01:02:43,431
to protect your children,

1074
01:02:43,455 --> 01:02:45,520
- or to get out of harm's way?
- [Angrily] Who are you

1075
01:02:45,544 --> 01:02:47,478
to tell me what kind of
wife and mother to be

1076
01:02:47,502 --> 01:02:48,915
when you are
neither one yourself?

1077
01:02:48,939 --> 01:02:51,700
You are a spinster. A whore!

1078
01:02:51,724 --> 01:02:53,136
- An unwed mother!
- Stop.

1079
01:02:53,160 --> 01:02:54,224
[Salome] Ona was
made unconscious

1080
01:02:54,248 --> 01:02:55,399
and raped like the rest of us.

1081
01:02:55,423 --> 01:02:57,837
How dare you call her a whore!

1082
01:02:57,861 --> 01:02:59,882
Mariche, are you not afraid
that your own sweet boys

1083
01:02:59,906 --> 01:03:01,275
will become monsters
like their father

1084
01:03:01,299 --> 01:03:02,798
because you do nothing
to protect them?

1085
01:03:02,822 --> 01:03:04,234
- Stop it!
- Nothing to educate them,

1086
01:03:04,258 --> 01:03:05,496
nothing to teach them

1087
01:03:05,520 --> 01:03:06,802
the horror of
their father's ways...

1088
01:03:06,826 --> 01:03:10,153
[Agata] I have heard enough!

1089
01:03:10,177 --> 01:03:13,591
Do you women realize
we are talking about leaving?

1090
01:03:13,615 --> 01:03:17,030
We are a large group.
Many things could go wrong.

1091
01:03:17,054 --> 01:03:18,248
And time is fleeting.

1092
01:03:18,272 --> 01:03:20,207
For the love
of our lord Jesus Christ

1093
01:03:20,231 --> 01:03:21,686
and precious savior,

1094
01:03:21,710 --> 01:03:24,235
shut your pie holes, please!

1095
01:03:29,414 --> 01:03:32,132
How dare you
pass judgment on me?

1096
01:03:32,156 --> 01:03:34,003
It wasn't a judgment.
It was a question.

1097
01:03:34,027 --> 01:03:35,072
[Scoffs]

1098
01:03:44,516 --> 01:03:46,387
[Agata whispers]
Tell her you're sorry.

1099
01:03:50,304 --> 01:03:52,282
I'm sorry.

1100
01:03:52,306 --> 01:03:53,631
I'm sorry that
what I said hurt you.

1101
01:03:53,655 --> 01:03:54,937
Oh, fuck it off!

1102
01:03:54,961 --> 01:03:56,199
Sit down, mariche!

1103
01:03:56,223 --> 01:03:57,592
It's "fuck off" I think.

1104
01:03:57,616 --> 01:03:58,660
Shh!

1105
01:04:00,227 --> 01:04:02,510
I am sorry.

1106
01:04:02,534 --> 01:04:04,729
I'm saying sorry, not just
to leave the hurt behind,

1107
01:04:04,753 --> 01:04:06,296
but because I feel truly

1108
01:04:06,320 --> 01:04:08,670
that I should not have
said something harmful to you.

1109
01:04:10,237 --> 01:04:11,693
And mariche, I'm sorry

1110
01:04:11,717 --> 01:04:15,068
because you do not
need or deserve any more harm.

1111
01:04:17,418 --> 01:04:18,985
Who are you?

1112
01:04:20,247 --> 01:04:22,075
Who are any of you

1113
01:04:23,033 --> 01:04:25,992
to pretend I have had a choice?

1114
01:04:43,140 --> 01:04:47,033
I am also sorry, mariche.

1115
01:04:47,057 --> 01:04:51,907
I didn't try to protect you
or your children from klaas.

1116
01:04:51,931 --> 01:04:55,563
And what you say is true.
You had no choice.

1117
01:04:55,587 --> 01:04:59,504
You forgave him,
again and again,

1118
01:05:00,244 --> 01:05:01,898
as you were told to.

1119
01:05:05,423 --> 01:05:07,120
As I told you to.

1120
01:05:09,253 --> 01:05:10,515
I'm sorry.

1121
01:05:12,299 --> 01:05:13,866
I'm sorry.

1122
01:05:16,913 --> 01:05:18,436
[Tearfully] I'm sorry.

1123
01:05:33,233 --> 01:05:34,365
[Breathes shakily]

1124
01:05:38,847 --> 01:05:40,260
It's not only the men and boys

1125
01:05:40,284 --> 01:05:42,503
who have been
excellent students.

1126
01:05:48,901 --> 01:05:49,902
[Sighs]

1127
01:05:54,689 --> 01:05:58,495
[Agata] I think mariche,
we are all very sorry.

1128
01:05:58,519 --> 01:06:01,150
What you were required
to endure was a...

1129
01:06:01,174 --> 01:06:03,979
Misuse of forgiveness.

1130
01:06:04,003 --> 01:06:05,720
Is there such a thing?

1131
01:06:05,744 --> 01:06:08,027
A forgiveness that is not good?

1132
01:06:08,051 --> 01:06:10,855
Perhaps forgiveness
can in some instances

1133
01:06:10,879 --> 01:06:13,795
be confused with permission.

1134
01:06:32,553 --> 01:06:35,252
[Sobbing quietly]

1135
01:06:40,953 --> 01:06:42,302
[Sobbing]

1136
01:06:47,307 --> 01:06:48,917
[Footsteps approaching]

1137
01:06:50,441 --> 01:06:51,896
[Greta] What in heaven's name?

1138
01:06:51,920 --> 01:06:53,855
[Boy whimpers]

1139
01:06:53,879 --> 01:06:55,620
What is it? Julius, what is it?

1140
01:06:59,189 --> 01:07:00,993
Nettie, please.
Make an exception

1141
01:07:01,017 --> 01:07:02,453
and tell us what is happening.

1142
01:07:03,541 --> 01:07:05,064
What has happened to him?

1143
01:07:06,631 --> 01:07:08,174
[Agata] Nettie, be realistic.

1144
01:07:08,198 --> 01:07:10,002
Tell us what has happened
to Julius.

1145
01:07:10,026 --> 01:07:11,505
Speak. Just this once.

1146
01:07:12,376 --> 01:07:13,962
What's wrong, sweetheart?

1147
01:07:13,986 --> 01:07:16,921
My nose.
There's a cherry up my nose.

1148
01:07:16,945 --> 01:07:18,706
Okay, well, blow.

1149
01:07:18,730 --> 01:07:21,187
- [Exhales]
- Harder. Again.

1150
01:07:21,211 --> 01:07:22,255
[Exhales]

1151
01:07:23,604 --> 01:07:24,799
[Mariche sighs in relief]

1152
01:07:24,823 --> 01:07:26,018
There you go.

1153
01:07:26,042 --> 01:07:27,913
We have no cherries
in the colony.

1154
01:07:28,609 --> 01:07:30,065
[Eerie music playing]

1155
01:07:30,089 --> 01:07:32,285
Klaas sometimes brings them
back from the city.

1156
01:07:32,309 --> 01:07:34,548
Who gave you
the cherries, Julius?

1157
01:07:34,572 --> 01:07:36,052
Papa.

1158
01:07:38,706 --> 01:07:39,901
Why don't you...

1159
01:07:39,925 --> 01:07:41,445
You go and play
with nettie, all right?

1160
01:07:48,803 --> 01:07:50,259
[Greta] Have we made a decision?

1161
01:07:50,283 --> 01:07:51,719
Are we leaving?

1162
01:07:53,721 --> 01:07:54,722
Yes.

1163
01:07:55,810 --> 01:07:56,831
We are leaving because...

1164
01:07:56,855 --> 01:07:58,093
We know why we are leaving.

1165
01:07:58,117 --> 01:08:00,076
We are leaving
because we cannot stay.

1166
01:08:03,992 --> 01:08:05,144
Hmm.

1167
01:08:05,168 --> 01:08:06,667
We will take young boys of 12
with us.

1168
01:08:06,691 --> 01:08:08,408
Allow the men
to join the women later

1169
01:08:08,432 --> 01:08:10,216
under certain conditions.

1170
01:08:10,869 --> 01:08:12,368
- No.
- No.

1171
01:08:12,392 --> 01:08:14,066
Aaron. I know.

1172
01:08:14,090 --> 01:08:16,198
Aaron is just over 12.
Just barely.

1173
01:08:16,222 --> 01:08:18,505
Why would boys
of 13 and 14 be left behind?

1174
01:08:18,529 --> 01:08:19,680
Why wouldn't they leave with us?

1175
01:08:19,704 --> 01:08:21,160
Surely, we don't
have to be afraid

1176
01:08:21,184 --> 01:08:22,509
of the boys of this age.

1177
01:08:22,533 --> 01:08:23,988
August, you're
the boys' teacher.

1178
01:08:24,012 --> 01:08:25,903
What is your feeling about this?

1179
01:08:25,927 --> 01:08:27,122
Do boys of that age

1180
01:08:27,146 --> 01:08:29,061
pose a risk
to our girls and women?

1181
01:08:33,283 --> 01:08:35,304
Yes. Possibly.

1182
01:08:35,328 --> 01:08:37,437
Boys of 13 or 14 are capable

1183
01:08:37,461 --> 01:08:40,290
of causing great damage
to girls and women.

1184
01:08:41,726 --> 01:08:43,510
And to each other.

1185
01:08:45,382 --> 01:08:47,403
It is a brash age.

1186
01:08:47,427 --> 01:08:50,841
They are possessed
of reckless urges,

1187
01:08:50,865 --> 01:08:52,495
physical exuberance,

1188
01:08:52,519 --> 01:08:56,760
intense curiosity
that often results in injury.

1189
01:08:56,784 --> 01:08:57,829
[Boys cheering]

1190
01:08:58,699 --> 01:09:00,938
Unbridled emotion,

1191
01:09:00,962 --> 01:09:04,159
including deep tenderness
and empathy,

1192
01:09:04,183 --> 01:09:05,508
and not quite enough

1193
01:09:05,532 --> 01:09:07,771
experience or brain development

1194
01:09:07,795 --> 01:09:09,947
to fully understand
or appreciate

1195
01:09:09,971 --> 01:09:12,820
the consequences
of their words or actions.

1196
01:09:12,844 --> 01:09:14,367
They are like the yearlings.

1197
01:09:15,760 --> 01:09:19,590
Young, awkward,
gleeful, powerful.

1198
01:09:21,244 --> 01:09:22,743
They're tall, muscular,

1199
01:09:22,767 --> 01:09:24,266
sexually inquisitive creatures,

1200
01:09:24,290 --> 01:09:27,511
with little impulse control,
but they are children.

1201
01:09:33,256 --> 01:09:35,388
They are children
and they can be taught.

1202
01:09:37,825 --> 01:09:40,064
I'm a two-bit schoolteacher,

1203
01:09:40,088 --> 01:09:41,892
a failed farmer,

1204
01:09:41,916 --> 01:09:45,200
and above all a believer.

1205
01:09:45,224 --> 01:09:48,116
And I believe
that with guidance,

1206
01:09:48,140 --> 01:09:51,337
firm love and Patience,

1207
01:09:51,361 --> 01:09:53,426
these boys are capable
of relearning

1208
01:09:53,450 --> 01:09:55,582
their roles as males
in the colony.

1209
01:10:02,807 --> 01:10:05,568
I believe in what the great poet

1210
01:10:05,592 --> 01:10:07,179
Samuel Taylor coleridge

1211
01:10:07,203 --> 01:10:10,206
thought were the cardinal
rules of early education.

1212
01:10:11,424 --> 01:10:12,947
"To work by love

1213
01:10:14,732 --> 01:10:17,082
"and so generate love.

1214
01:10:18,170 --> 01:10:19,582
"To habituate the mind

1215
01:10:19,606 --> 01:10:21,826
"to intellectual
accuracy and truth.

1216
01:10:22,827 --> 01:10:25,873
"To excite imaginative power."

1217
01:10:28,528 --> 01:10:29,679
[Laughing]

1218
01:10:29,703 --> 01:10:31,377
He said,

1219
01:10:31,401 --> 01:10:35,903
"little is taught
by contest or dispute,

1220
01:10:35,927 --> 01:10:39,191
"everything by
sympathy and love."

1221
01:10:48,896 --> 01:10:51,179
I believe the boys
should be allowed

1222
01:10:51,203 --> 01:10:52,683
to leave with the women...

1223
01:10:55,773 --> 01:10:58,404
Providing the women
choose to leave.

1224
01:10:58,428 --> 01:11:00,101
[Mariche] It was a yes
or no question.

1225
01:11:00,125 --> 01:11:03,346
You shit like any other man,
why don't you talk like one?

1226
01:11:07,437 --> 01:11:08,438
Sorry.

1227
01:11:11,179 --> 01:11:13,288
[Agata] I have a proposal
to make.

1228
01:11:13,312 --> 01:11:15,986
We have to protect
all of our children.

1229
01:11:16,010 --> 01:11:17,727
Not only our daughters.

1230
01:11:17,751 --> 01:11:20,252
Every boy under 15

1231
01:11:20,276 --> 01:11:22,210
and the ones
who need special care

1232
01:11:22,234 --> 01:11:24,473
must accompany the women.

1233
01:11:24,497 --> 01:11:25,909
How do you mean must?

1234
01:11:25,933 --> 01:11:27,171
What if they refuse?

1235
01:11:27,195 --> 01:11:28,390
What if they
don't want to leave?

1236
01:11:28,414 --> 01:11:31,480
We can't carry teenagers
on our backs.

1237
01:11:31,504 --> 01:11:33,917
We will try
to influence our sons.

1238
01:11:33,941 --> 01:11:35,354
But we cannot force them,

1239
01:11:35,378 --> 01:11:37,356
and they might refuse,
it's true.

1240
01:11:37,380 --> 01:11:38,598
August...

1241
01:11:40,687 --> 01:11:44,300
You would stay and teach
the boys who remain?

1242
01:11:45,388 --> 01:11:46,388
Of course.

1243
01:12:02,666 --> 01:12:04,296
[Autje] He's right outside.

1244
01:12:04,320 --> 01:12:05,625
[Tense music playing]

1245
01:12:06,626 --> 01:12:07,932
Klaas?

1246
01:12:11,544 --> 01:12:12,565
[Greta gasps]

1247
01:12:12,589 --> 01:12:14,199
He has Ruth and Cheryl.

1248
01:12:16,767 --> 01:12:19,659
Everybody, back to your houses
and pack up.

1249
01:12:19,683 --> 01:12:22,314
If anyone asks,
we were quilting.

1250
01:12:22,338 --> 01:12:25,273
August, uh, get the map.

1251
01:12:25,297 --> 01:12:26,492
Neitje and autje,

1252
01:12:26,516 --> 01:12:28,407
you must run right now
to every house

1253
01:12:28,431 --> 01:12:29,973
and tell the women,
we are leaving.

1254
01:12:29,997 --> 01:12:31,235
[Salome] Tell them to pack up
everything they can

1255
01:12:31,259 --> 01:12:32,367
and to meet us
outside the washhouse

1256
01:12:32,391 --> 01:12:33,977
an hour after sunrise.

1257
01:12:34,001 --> 01:12:35,414
[Agata] We need to get
an early start in the morning.

1258
01:12:35,438 --> 01:12:38,025
Let's all meet back here
at sunrise.

1259
01:12:38,049 --> 01:12:39,093
All of us.

1260
01:12:42,270 --> 01:12:43,596
An hour after sunrise.

1261
01:12:43,620 --> 01:12:45,032
We congregate on the road
by the washhouse.

1262
01:12:45,056 --> 01:12:47,275
- Do we bring...
- Everything. Bring everything.

1263
01:12:47,841 --> 01:12:48,929
Why?

1264
01:12:56,937 --> 01:12:58,698
- After sunrise... all right?
- Wake up.

1265
01:12:58,722 --> 01:13:00,439
Tomorrow one hour after sunrise.

1266
01:13:00,463 --> 01:13:01,594
We're leaving after sunrise.

1267
01:13:04,162 --> 01:13:05,337
[Knock at door]

1268
01:13:20,526 --> 01:13:23,070
[Panting]

1269
01:13:23,094 --> 01:13:25,289
We meet an hour after sunrise
on this road.

1270
01:13:25,313 --> 01:13:26,465
Bring your buggies.

1271
01:13:26,489 --> 01:13:27,925
Thank you, sister.

1272
01:13:35,367 --> 01:13:36,847
[Girls laughing]

1273
01:13:37,761 --> 01:13:39,434
[Kisses]

1274
01:13:39,458 --> 01:13:40,566
[Girl talking indistinctly]

1275
01:13:40,590 --> 01:13:42,350
Who can get home
the quickest, huh?

1276
01:13:42,374 --> 01:13:44,439
[Girl] She has a cricket
in her hands.

1277
01:13:44,463 --> 01:13:45,595
[Mariche] You do?

1278
01:13:47,292 --> 01:13:49,139
Can I see? Okay.

1279
01:13:49,163 --> 01:13:51,078
[Children speaking indistinctly]

1280
01:13:55,474 --> 01:13:56,736
[Mariche] Yes. Bed time.

1281
01:13:57,258 --> 01:13:58,366
Yes.

1282
01:13:58,390 --> 01:14:00,150
[Greta] Don't go.

1283
01:14:00,174 --> 01:14:04,154
Stay with me tonight.
Or I will go with you.

1284
01:14:04,178 --> 01:14:06,592
If I don't go home, it'll draw
attention to all of us.

1285
01:14:06,616 --> 01:14:09,159
- Mariche.
- Go home, mother.

1286
01:14:09,183 --> 01:14:11,055
I'll see you at sunrise.

1287
01:14:50,094 --> 01:14:52,028
[Autje] They said later,
it should have taken longer

1288
01:14:52,052 --> 01:14:53,750
to pack up a whole life.

1289
01:14:54,664 --> 01:14:56,337
It was disappointing

1290
01:14:56,361 --> 01:14:58,644
to realize that everything
that ever mattered to you

1291
01:14:58,668 --> 01:15:00,452
could be gathered up
in a few short hours.

1292
01:15:04,587 --> 01:15:07,198
We would leave
only traces of ourselves.

1293
01:15:22,605 --> 01:15:24,084
Go. Go.

1294
01:15:25,608 --> 01:15:26,652
[Tense music fades]

1295
01:15:32,484 --> 01:15:34,355
[Ona whispering] Psst. August!

1296
01:15:36,662 --> 01:15:38,011
Come sit with me.

1297
01:15:42,799 --> 01:15:44,159
[August whispering]
Here's the map.

1298
01:15:47,891 --> 01:15:49,153
Where are we?

1299
01:15:51,808 --> 01:15:52,896
Here.

1300
01:15:54,201 --> 01:15:55,222
[Ona] Here?

1301
01:15:55,246 --> 01:15:56,290
[August] Mm-hmm.

1302
01:15:57,596 --> 01:15:59,467
This is where we are.

1303
01:16:01,948 --> 01:16:02,993
[Ona chuckles]

1304
01:16:06,431 --> 01:16:11,610
This is north, south,
east, and west.

1305
01:16:12,263 --> 01:16:13,588
But the map moves.

1306
01:16:13,612 --> 01:16:15,875
How do you know
which way it should be facing?

1307
01:16:17,137 --> 01:16:19,487
Celestial navigation.

1308
01:16:20,140 --> 01:16:21,794
I can show you.

1309
01:16:22,665 --> 01:16:23,840
[Mellow music playing]

1310
01:16:27,626 --> 01:16:29,212
Do you know
of the southern cross?

1311
01:16:29,236 --> 01:16:30,281
[Ona] Mm-hmm.

1312
01:16:31,151 --> 01:16:32,389
You and the women

1313
01:16:32,413 --> 01:16:35,852
can use the southern cross
to navigate.

1314
01:16:37,288 --> 01:16:39,396
If you, um,

1315
01:16:39,420 --> 01:16:42,467
make your right hand
into a fist...

1316
01:16:46,689 --> 01:16:51,563
Align the first knuckle
with the axis of the cross.

1317
01:16:53,043 --> 01:16:56,239
And then the tip
of your thumb here

1318
01:16:56,263 --> 01:16:58,048
will indicate south.

1319
01:16:59,179 --> 01:17:00,354
[Both chuckle]

1320
01:17:08,798 --> 01:17:10,800
Will you show the others?

1321
01:17:12,671 --> 01:17:15,413
We will have
a lesson in navigation.

1322
01:17:17,545 --> 01:17:20,481
Did you already know
about this little trick?

1323
01:17:20,505 --> 01:17:21,680
[Laughing]

1324
01:17:23,160 --> 01:17:24,616
Of course, I did.

1325
01:17:24,640 --> 01:17:26,574
I wish there was something
I could teach you

1326
01:17:26,598 --> 01:17:29,142
that you didn't already know.

1327
01:17:29,166 --> 01:17:30,558
[August chuckles]

1328
01:17:49,926 --> 01:17:52,687
What will become of you
when we leave?

1329
01:17:52,711 --> 01:17:54,539
[Mellow music continues]

1330
01:18:17,257 --> 01:18:20,802
You make a fist
with your right hand.

1331
01:18:20,826 --> 01:18:24,719
And point your two knuckles
to the southern cross.

1332
01:18:24,743 --> 01:18:27,441
It's called
celestial navigation.

1333
01:18:33,970 --> 01:18:36,059
Point these two knuckles.

1334
01:18:40,803 --> 01:18:41,867
Like that?

1335
01:18:41,891 --> 01:18:42,935
Mm-hmm.

1336
01:18:48,419 --> 01:18:50,900
And wherever your thumb
is pointing that's south.

1337
01:19:08,439 --> 01:19:11,461
[Autje] We like to put
frames around things.

1338
01:19:11,485 --> 01:19:14,813
Even when they
are spilling out the edges.

1339
01:19:14,837 --> 01:19:17,772
So, we gathered
one last time in the hayloft,

1340
01:19:17,796 --> 01:19:19,426
where so much had been said.

1341
01:19:19,450 --> 01:19:21,123
[Agata humming]

1342
01:19:21,147 --> 01:19:22,995
So much that your grandmother
would have told you,

1343
01:19:23,019 --> 01:19:24,498
had you ever met.

1344
01:19:25,195 --> 01:19:26,413
[Mariche groaning]

1345
01:19:34,595 --> 01:19:35,596
[Mellow music fades]

1346
01:19:46,956 --> 01:19:48,087
[Greta] Is he gone?

1347
01:19:49,872 --> 01:19:51,719
He's sleeping.

1348
01:19:51,743 --> 01:19:53,266
Dead to the world.

1349
01:19:55,399 --> 01:19:57,183
He was very drunk.

1350
01:20:00,230 --> 01:20:01,381
And he caught me

1351
01:20:01,405 --> 01:20:03,711
sneaking back
into the house late,

1352
01:20:05,148 --> 01:20:06,473
and then he went to the barn

1353
01:20:06,497 --> 01:20:09,650
and found we had
taken the horses.

1354
01:20:09,674 --> 01:20:13,785
[Salome] Mariche, did you
tell him what we are planning?

1355
01:20:13,809 --> 01:20:15,699
She did. But only because
he wouldn't stop hitting me

1356
01:20:15,723 --> 01:20:17,397
and she was trying
to distract him.

1357
01:20:17,421 --> 01:20:19,616
[Mariche] I don't think
he believed me.

1358
01:20:19,640 --> 01:20:21,836
And even if he did,
I don't think he'll remember.

1359
01:20:21,860 --> 01:20:24,080
He'll be passed out
all morning I'm sure.

1360
01:20:27,692 --> 01:20:30,956
But I also told him because
I suddenly felt very...

1361
01:20:34,917 --> 01:20:35,918
[Chuckles]

1362
01:20:46,406 --> 01:20:48,756
We have decided that we want...

1363
01:20:51,759 --> 01:20:52,935
That we are...

1364
01:20:55,459 --> 01:20:58,592
We are entitled to three things.

1365
01:21:01,421 --> 01:21:02,596
[Greta] What are they?

1366
01:21:07,819 --> 01:21:10,300
We want our children to be safe.

1367
01:21:22,616 --> 01:21:23,811
We want...

1368
01:21:23,835 --> 01:21:27,621
We want to be steadfast
in our faith.

1369
01:21:31,147 --> 01:21:33,279
And we want to think.

1370
01:21:36,804 --> 01:21:37,805
[Greta] Yes.

1371
01:21:41,635 --> 01:21:43,115
Praise god.

1372
01:21:43,986 --> 01:21:45,030
[Chuckles softly]

1373
01:22:05,442 --> 01:22:07,313
Yeah. We all want that.

1374
01:22:08,662 --> 01:22:14,296
[Singing]
♪ nearer, my god, to thee ♪

1375
01:22:14,320 --> 01:22:18,735
- ♪ nearer to thee ♪
- ♪ to thee ♪

1376
01:22:18,759 --> 01:22:24,350
[Women singing]
♪ e'en though it be a cross ♪

1377
01:22:24,374 --> 01:22:27,594
♪ that raiseth me ♪

1378
01:22:29,509 --> 01:22:34,360
♪ still all my song shall be ♪

1379
01:22:34,384 --> 01:22:42,384
♪ nearer, my god, to thee ♪

1380
01:22:46,048 --> 01:22:50,269
♪ nearer to thee ♪

1381
01:22:52,315 --> 01:22:56,493
♪ though like the wanderer ♪

1382
01:22:57,885 --> 01:23:01,933
♪ the sun gone down ♪

1383
01:23:03,848 --> 01:23:09,612
♪ darkness be over me ♪

1384
01:23:09,636 --> 01:23:13,553
♪ my rest a stone ♪

1385
01:23:15,599 --> 01:23:19,211
♪ yet in my dreams I'd be ♪

1386
01:23:21,257 --> 01:23:29,257
♪ nearer, my god, to thee ♪

1387
01:23:32,920 --> 01:23:38,076
♪ nearer to thee ♪

1388
01:23:38,100 --> 01:23:39,207
[Breath trembling]

1389
01:23:39,231 --> 01:23:44,106
♪ There let the way appear ♪

1390
01:23:45,281 --> 01:23:49,024
♪ steps unto heav'n ♪

1391
01:23:50,938 --> 01:23:56,659
♪ all that thou sendest me ♪

1392
01:23:56,683 --> 01:24:02,143
♪ in mercy giv'n ♪

1393
01:24:02,167 --> 01:24:03,473
[Neitje] Let's go.

1394
01:24:05,127 --> 01:24:06,452
I saw your brother.

1395
01:24:06,476 --> 01:24:07,888
Careful! We're gonna get you.

1396
01:24:07,912 --> 01:24:10,021
Help me, I'm tied up.

1397
01:24:10,045 --> 01:24:11,325
[Children speaking indistinctly]

1398
01:24:12,177 --> 01:24:13,396
Where are they?

1399
01:24:15,528 --> 01:24:16,747
Look there.

1400
01:24:19,924 --> 01:24:23,362
[Women singing]
♪ nearer to thee ♪

1401
01:24:25,712 --> 01:24:31,825
♪ nearer, my god, to thee ♪

1402
01:24:31,849 --> 01:24:37,159
♪ nearer to thee ♪

1403
01:24:52,870 --> 01:24:54,326
Just...

1404
01:24:54,350 --> 01:24:55,849
August, you can speak
whenever you want.

1405
01:24:55,873 --> 01:24:58,223
You don't have
to raise your hand.

1406
01:25:01,008 --> 01:25:02,009
I...

1407
01:25:05,839 --> 01:25:07,232
It's all right.

1408
01:25:09,321 --> 01:25:10,801
It wasn't important.

1409
01:25:12,585 --> 01:25:14,718
[Footsteps approaching]

1410
01:25:17,590 --> 01:25:18,939
[Greta] Oh.

1411
01:25:22,117 --> 01:25:24,119
Are the children
clean and ready?

1412
01:25:28,949 --> 01:25:30,864
Thank you, Melvin.

1413
01:25:33,171 --> 01:25:35,260
Thank you for saying my name.

1414
01:25:37,784 --> 01:25:39,980
We hid Ruth and Cheryl for you.

1415
01:25:40,004 --> 01:25:41,373
They are ready to go.

1416
01:25:41,397 --> 01:25:42,920
Really?

1417
01:25:43,573 --> 01:25:46,619
Well, oh, my girls.

1418
01:25:48,969 --> 01:25:50,754
Has Aaron readied
the horses for us?

1419
01:25:53,670 --> 01:25:54,975
What? Well, where is he?

1420
01:25:56,977 --> 01:25:58,065
Where is he?

1421
01:25:58,762 --> 01:26:00,261
- No.
- Speak to me.

1422
01:26:00,285 --> 01:26:01,828
- [Agata] You're safe, Melvin.
- Please, speak to me.

1423
01:26:01,852 --> 01:26:02,829
No, no, no. I won't harm you.
I'm not your enemy!

1424
01:26:02,853 --> 01:26:03,873
You have to be calm, salome.

1425
01:26:03,897 --> 01:26:05,788
- No!
- Aaron will be found.

1426
01:26:05,812 --> 01:26:07,510
I'm not leaving without him.

1427
01:26:11,601 --> 01:26:13,907
[Agata] Salome, come back!

1428
01:26:17,824 --> 01:26:19,739
[Ona] What if she
doesn't convince him?

1429
01:26:23,439 --> 01:26:24,440
Mother?

1430
01:26:25,267 --> 01:26:27,506
[Gasping]

1431
01:26:27,530 --> 01:26:28,574
Breathe.

1432
01:26:29,401 --> 01:26:30,489
Breathe.

1433
01:26:32,361 --> 01:26:34,972
[All breathing heavily]

1434
01:26:36,756 --> 01:26:38,280
We are going to go now.

1435
01:26:39,019 --> 01:26:40,412
[Ona sobbing]

1436
01:26:43,154 --> 01:26:45,263
I'm all right. Please go.

1437
01:26:45,287 --> 01:26:47,767
Come on, let's go.

1438
01:26:49,029 --> 01:26:50,030
Now?

1439
01:26:50,553 --> 01:26:51,554
Yes.

1440
01:26:52,424 --> 01:26:53,773
Make a list, August.

1441
01:26:55,297 --> 01:26:56,752
A list of what?

1442
01:26:56,776 --> 01:26:58,232
[Agata] Of good things.

1443
01:26:58,256 --> 01:27:00,495
Of plans, of memories.

1444
01:27:00,519 --> 01:27:02,695
Whatever you feel
goes into a good list.

1445
01:27:03,653 --> 01:27:05,718
What we, the women
will want there.

1446
01:27:05,742 --> 01:27:06,786
Please write it down.

1447
01:27:09,093 --> 01:27:10,268
August.

1448
01:27:11,965 --> 01:27:14,596
Thank you for all you've done.

1449
01:27:14,620 --> 01:27:17,251
We are all so proud of you.

1450
01:27:17,275 --> 01:27:18,581
[Crying]

1451
01:27:22,976 --> 01:27:25,501
And your mother
would be proud too.

1452
01:27:32,769 --> 01:27:34,292
I'll make a list.

1453
01:27:37,208 --> 01:27:39,317
This is going
to be a difficult trip.

1454
01:27:39,341 --> 01:27:42,213
Today is the day
the lord hath made.

1455
01:27:43,736 --> 01:27:44,998
Rejoice...

1456
01:27:47,349 --> 01:27:48,741
And be glad in it.

1457
01:27:53,268 --> 01:27:54,965
Go join the others.

1458
01:27:55,879 --> 01:27:57,054
Please.

1459
01:28:06,585 --> 01:28:09,434
I will not be buried
in this colony.

1460
01:28:09,458 --> 01:28:11,436
[Crying and laughing]

1461
01:28:11,460 --> 01:28:15,202
Get me into a buggy now
and let me die on the trail.

1462
01:28:16,508 --> 01:28:18,399
But what about August?

1463
01:28:18,423 --> 01:28:19,511
[Agata] Oh!

1464
01:28:24,124 --> 01:28:25,430
He'll be fine.

1465
01:28:32,045 --> 01:28:33,656
He'll be fine.

1466
01:28:55,417 --> 01:28:56,722
Hang on with both hands.

1467
01:28:58,376 --> 01:28:59,377
[August chuckles]

1468
01:29:08,778 --> 01:29:09,779
[August] Ona!

1469
01:29:10,997 --> 01:29:12,303
[Emotional music playing]

1470
01:29:15,915 --> 01:29:17,395
I will always love you.

1471
01:29:19,832 --> 01:29:21,356
[Chuckles softly]

1472
01:29:40,157 --> 01:29:42,570
She loves you too, August.

1473
01:29:42,594 --> 01:29:44,509
She loves everyone.

1474
01:29:48,208 --> 01:29:49,427
[Breath trembling]

1475
01:30:23,679 --> 01:30:25,289
[Agata] Sun.

1476
01:30:29,598 --> 01:30:31,251
[Neitje] Stars.

1477
01:30:33,863 --> 01:30:35,473
[Miep] Pails.

1478
01:30:38,476 --> 01:30:40,130
[Mariche] The harvest.

1479
01:30:43,742 --> 01:30:45,265
[Salome] Numbers.

1480
01:30:47,398 --> 01:30:48,660
[Ona] Window.

1481
01:30:51,141 --> 01:30:52,466
[Greta] Straw.

1482
01:30:52,490 --> 01:30:54,990
[Children chattering]

1483
01:30:55,014 --> 01:30:56,407
[Autje] Sounds.

1484
01:30:59,628 --> 01:31:01,194
[Ona] Beams.

1485
01:31:07,026 --> 01:31:08,439
[Salome] Love.

1486
01:31:08,463 --> 01:31:09,507
[Spraying]

1487
01:31:11,683 --> 01:31:13,946
All right. We'll go.

1488
01:31:21,388 --> 01:31:22,694
[Neitje] Language.

1489
01:31:26,481 --> 01:31:27,873
[Autje] Wind.

1490
01:31:32,617 --> 01:31:34,010
[August] Women.

1491
01:31:36,795 --> 01:31:37,796
[Clanging]

1492
01:31:43,672 --> 01:31:44,847
Salome?

1493
01:31:46,892 --> 01:31:47,893
[Emotional music fades]

1494
01:31:49,068 --> 01:31:50,766
We may need
to protect ourselves.

1495
01:31:52,724 --> 01:31:53,769
Where is Aaron?

1496
01:31:55,205 --> 01:31:56,989
He's in the buggy, waiting.

1497
01:31:58,077 --> 01:31:59,731
You convinced him to leave?

1498
01:32:01,254 --> 01:32:02,473
You may need this.

1499
01:32:03,909 --> 01:32:05,215
For protection.

1500
01:32:06,912 --> 01:32:08,000
Did you?

1501
01:32:10,437 --> 01:32:11,893
- Did you have...?
- Yes!

1502
01:32:11,917 --> 01:32:14,093
He's coming with me.
He's my child.

1503
01:32:26,497 --> 01:32:27,672
Goodbye, August.

1504
01:32:29,674 --> 01:32:30,806
Good luck.

1505
01:32:32,242 --> 01:32:35,090
Please take care
of ona and her baby.

1506
01:32:35,114 --> 01:32:37,005
Of course. I promise.

1507
01:32:37,029 --> 01:32:38,833
Wait. I need
to give you something.

1508
01:32:38,857 --> 01:32:40,380
[Salome] No! I have to go!

1509
01:32:46,909 --> 01:32:47,910
Here.

1510
01:32:51,783 --> 01:32:53,350
Why have you got a gun, August?

1511
01:32:58,485 --> 01:32:59,574
[Crying]

1512
01:33:08,321 --> 01:33:10,193
Don't kill yourself, August.

1513
01:33:11,542 --> 01:33:13,500
You have important work to do.

1514
01:33:14,501 --> 01:33:15,546
[Sniffles]

1515
01:33:16,808 --> 01:33:19,985
You are the boys' teacher.

1516
01:33:31,388 --> 01:33:32,607
Don't come back.

1517
01:33:34,130 --> 01:33:36,132
Don't ever come back.
Any of you.

1518
01:33:41,746 --> 01:33:43,071
Oh, wait. I need...

1519
01:33:43,095 --> 01:33:44,357
No.

1520
01:33:47,360 --> 01:33:48,468
Please.

1521
01:33:48,492 --> 01:33:50,818
Please, salome,
give these to ona.

1522
01:33:50,842 --> 01:33:52,452
But, no...
But she can't read them.

1523
01:33:53,323 --> 01:33:55,020
Her child will read them.

1524
01:33:56,587 --> 01:33:58,696
No, August.

1525
01:33:58,720 --> 01:34:02,375
The purpose was for you
to take the minutes.

1526
01:34:09,861 --> 01:34:10,862
[Emotional music playing]

1527
01:34:16,389 --> 01:34:17,739
We'll meet again.

1528
01:34:18,740 --> 01:34:20,045
We'll meet again.

1529
01:34:35,757 --> 01:34:37,933
[Women talking indistinctly]

1530
01:34:54,253 --> 01:34:56,038
[Children chattering]

1531
01:34:57,779 --> 01:34:59,452
[Woman 1] Girls, now,
those can go in the back.

1532
01:34:59,476 --> 01:35:00,607
That's fine.

1533
01:35:02,261 --> 01:35:04,718
[Woman 2] We have
more room back here.

1534
01:35:04,742 --> 01:35:05,862
[Woman 3] No, but thank you.

1535
01:35:06,962 --> 01:35:08,635
[Woman 4] Do you have
any more room?

1536
01:35:08,659 --> 01:35:10,269
[Woman 5] We have room
for one more.

1537
01:35:11,967 --> 01:35:14,075
Or two little ones.

1538
01:35:14,099 --> 01:35:15,710
[Woman 6] She can sit on my lap.

1539
01:35:17,886 --> 01:35:19,341
[Woman 7] It's sturdy now.

1540
01:35:19,365 --> 01:35:21,193
[Woman 1] Come with me.
Follow me.

1541
01:35:23,587 --> 01:35:25,739
[Woman 8] It's all right,
sisters. It's all right.

1542
01:35:25,763 --> 01:35:27,243
[Chickens clucking]

1543
01:35:33,205 --> 01:35:35,381
[Woman 9] Up, up. There you go.

1544
01:35:36,426 --> 01:35:38,012
[Woman 10] Hold the baby
for now.

1545
01:35:38,036 --> 01:35:39,666
[Woman 11] You'll be riding
with your brother.

1546
01:35:39,690 --> 01:35:40,667
[Woman 12] I need a little
more rope to tie this down.

1547
01:35:40,691 --> 01:35:41,811
[Woman 13] I have some here.

1548
01:35:49,004 --> 01:35:50,135
[Woman 14] Are we all in?

1549
01:36:03,322 --> 01:36:04,323
[Woman 1] All right.

1550
01:36:09,024 --> 01:36:10,286
[Panting]

1551
01:36:17,772 --> 01:36:19,512
[Autje] So happy. Come on.

1552
01:36:20,470 --> 01:36:21,688
Come on. Here.

1553
01:36:29,261 --> 01:36:30,456
[Helena sighs in relief]

1554
01:36:30,480 --> 01:36:32,134
[Panting]

1555
01:36:40,359 --> 01:36:41,796
[Chuckles]

1556
01:37:37,895 --> 01:37:39,114
[Ona] Shh, shh, shh.

1557
01:37:40,419 --> 01:37:41,943
[Humming]

1558
01:37:43,466 --> 01:37:45,009
- [Emotional music fades]
- [Baby gurgling]

1559
01:37:45,033 --> 01:37:48,253
[Autje] Your story will be
different from ours.

1560
01:38:45,528 --> 01:38:46,616
[Mellow music playing]

1561
01:41:29,039 --> 01:41:30,345
[Mellow music fades]

1562
01:43:05,918 --> 01:43:07,006
[Children singing]

1563
01:43:53,923 --> 01:43:54,924
[Singing stops]
